262
00:14:18,631 --> 00:14:20,461
It takes too long.

263
00:14:20,461 --> 00:14:22,341
It takes more than an hour.

264
00:14:22,341 --> 00:14:24,001
- Right now?
- Yes.

265
00:14:24,001 --> 00:14:26,991
I looked up how long
it'll take to get to your work.

266
00:14:26,991 --> 00:14:29,121
It'll take an hour and nine minutes.

267
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,391
It's okay.

268
00:14:31,391 --> 00:14:35,071
- No, so...
- It's okay.

269
00:14:35,071 --> 00:14:38,021
- Did you eat?
- Eat? What do you mean?

270
00:14:38,021 --> 00:14:41,131
- I thought you came down early.
- I did come down early.

271
00:14:41,131 --> 00:14:45,351
- She wanted to eat with you.
- I heard the alarm, but I fell back asleep.

272
00:14:46,341 --> 00:14:48,031
You look puffy.

273
00:14:48,031 --> 00:14:50,091
I puffed up a lot.

274
00:14:50,091 --> 00:14:51,911
Granola?

275
00:14:53,231 --> 00:14:55,631
Choco Chex.

276
00:14:59,211 --> 00:15:01,991
Do you want the small choco balls?

277
00:15:01,991 --> 00:15:02,991
[Turning his head]

278
00:15:04,631 --> 00:15:05,871
[Looking down]

279
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:07,991
You're hiding your face, aren't you?

280
00:15:07,991 --> 00:15:09,621
[Hehe]

281
00:15:09,621 --> 00:15:12,191
This is how you look when you're puffy.

282
00:15:12,191 --> 00:15:13,941
[Looking down]

283
00:15:14,441 --> 00:15:17,831
Gosh, you can't see me like this already.

284
00:15:24,421 --> 00:15:27,521
- Is it an extreme case?
- Yeah.

285
00:15:29,241 --> 00:15:34,541
I didn't think you'd see me like this so soon.

286
00:15:38,781 --> 00:15:41,981
I want to run away. Should I not drive you?

287
00:15:45,941 --> 00:15:46,961
[Laughing]

288
00:15:48,091 --> 00:15:49,891
[Gyu Ri is getting ready for work]

289
00:15:49,891 --> 00:15:52,671
Hold on. She can't see them.

290
00:15:52,671 --> 00:15:54,211
What if she runs into them?

291
00:15:54,211 --> 00:15:56,501
I'm the same.

292
00:15:56,501 --> 00:15:59,601
I don't look so great.

293
00:15:59,601 --> 00:16:01,421
How many hours did you sleep?

294
00:16:01,421 --> 00:16:04,801
- I don't think I slept at all.
- Gosh, that bad?

295
00:16:04,801 --> 00:16:07,441
I only blinked briefly.

296
00:16:07,441 --> 00:16:10,791
I just... I just woke up.

297
00:16:12,811 --> 00:16:14,611
Why? Because you drank?

298
00:16:14,611 --> 00:16:17,281
No, it's just that...

299
00:16:17,281 --> 00:16:19,901
I woke up whenever I started falling asleep.

300
00:16:19,901 --> 00:16:21,861
That's how shocked she was.

301
00:16:21,861 --> 00:16:23,421
[Staring]

302
00:16:33,151 --> 00:16:34,981
- It takes 12 minutes.
- No!

303
00:16:34,981 --> 00:16:37,541
From here right now?

304
00:16:37,541 --> 00:16:39,921
Should we leave at 8:10?

305
00:16:41,681 --> 00:16:42,281
[Smiling]

306
00:16:43,171 --> 00:16:45,451
Did you sleep well?

307
00:16:46,461 --> 00:16:47,661
[Turning around]

308
00:16:47,661 --> 00:16:52,401
- Gyu Ri didn't get his text last night.
- Right.

309
00:16:52,401 --> 00:16:53,771
[Smiling]

310
00:16:54,411 --> 00:16:58,611
Isn't anyone else going to work?

311
00:17:02,521 --> 00:17:06,531
They are, but I think later.

312
00:17:08,121 --> 00:17:13,221
Jun Hyeon will probably come downstairs soon.

313
00:17:13,221 --> 00:17:14,861
[Looking]

314
00:17:18,311 --> 00:17:23,101
[They stopped talking when Gyu Ri showed up]

315
00:17:27,301 --> 00:17:30,221
[Gyu Ri is putting her bag next to Wu Yeol]

316
00:17:40,551 --> 00:17:42,221
[Concerned]

317
00:17:51,041 --> 00:17:53,941
[Awkward atmosphere]

318
00:18:03,591 --> 00:18:06,491
I haven't had cereal in the morning in a while.

319
00:18:07,941 --> 00:18:09,741
I know. Same.

320
00:18:10,591 --> 00:18:12,781
What do you have for breakfast?

321
00:18:12,781 --> 00:18:14,931
What do you have for breakfast?

322
00:18:16,421 --> 00:18:19,061
- Some probiotic.
- Gyu Ri appears cold somehow.

323
00:18:19,061 --> 00:18:21,481
[Quietly listening to Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong]

324
00:18:25,211 --> 00:18:31,561
[Starting the morning with a slight tension]

325
00:18:32,701 --> 00:18:36,151
It doesn't take that long.
It takes 12 minutes from here.

326
00:18:36,151 --> 00:18:39,991
It takes 25 minutes from there to my work.

327
00:18:39,991 --> 00:18:42,371
- But...
- Just in case?

328
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:45,091
It takes too long from the school.

329
00:18:45,091 --> 00:18:46,911
You have to go further north.

330
00:18:46,911 --> 00:18:48,871
I didn't think of that.

331
00:18:48,871 --> 00:18:51,281
I was so worried about it.

332
00:18:53,701 --> 00:18:55,581
It doesn't matter to me.

333
00:18:55,581 --> 00:18:57,821
[Against it]

334
00:19:00,011 --> 00:19:02,311
It feels different.

335
00:19:02,311 --> 00:19:05,101
You keep...

336
00:19:06,981 --> 00:19:08,951
No, I don't want it.

337
00:19:08,951 --> 00:19:10,911
That's what I thought.

338
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:14,151
She won't even look at them.

339
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:18,151
Is there a direct line from there?

340
00:19:18,151 --> 00:19:21,501
- What's this? Is this a movie?
- Is there?

341
00:19:22,501 --> 00:19:25,451
[Day 2 - Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri's carpool]

342
00:19:26,851 --> 00:19:28,961
Which line do you take of the two?

343
00:19:28,961 --> 00:19:31,721
[Remembering that day]

344
00:19:32,511 --> 00:19:34,581
Wow, daebak.

345
00:19:38,391 --> 00:19:39,991
[Glancing]

346
00:19:40,711 --> 00:19:42,861
There isn't any, right?

347
00:19:42,861 --> 00:19:45,091
Why did you pick that stop? Line No. 2?

348
00:19:45,091 --> 00:19:46,931
- Line No. 4.
- Because it's Line No. 4?

349
00:19:46,931 --> 00:19:52,471
I usually take a bus from Hyehwa Station.

350
00:19:52,471 --> 00:19:54,821
See you in the evening, Unni.

351
00:20:03,351 --> 00:20:04,191
[Staring]

352
00:20:07,181 --> 00:20:10,011
[Mysterious feelings]

353
00:20:11,951 --> 00:20:13,501
I'm not puffy at all.

354
00:20:13,501 --> 00:20:16,471
It's okay. You can get puffy.

355
00:20:16,471 --> 00:20:19,911
[They loosen up as soon as Gyu Ri leaves]

356
00:20:20,721 --> 00:20:24,241
[Gyu Ri is leaving while hearing them talking]

357
00:20:25,231 --> 00:20:26,541
[Looking]

358
00:20:31,421 --> 00:20:33,361
Gosh, so scary.

359
00:20:33,361 --> 00:20:35,311
I can't watch it. I can't.

360
00:20:35,311 --> 00:20:38,891
Gyu Ri was anxious on the
first day. She's like that.

361
00:20:38,891 --> 00:20:41,751
Her eyes were on everything but them.

362
00:20:41,751 --> 00:20:44,241
She looked at them briefly and left.

363
00:20:44,241 --> 00:20:47,491
Gyu Ri had a bit of a scary vibe.

364
00:20:47,491 --> 00:20:51,021
He's been texting her except for last night.

365
00:20:51,021 --> 00:20:54,721
- He could feel a bit guilty.
- It must bother him.

366
00:20:56,491 --> 00:21:01,591
[Going to work alone this time]

367
00:21:02,051 --> 00:21:04,321
When we carpooled...

368
00:21:04,321 --> 00:21:06,731
- See you.
- Bye.

369
00:21:06,731 --> 00:21:09,681
When I got off and waved goodbye,

370
00:21:09,681 --> 00:21:14,011
I wasn't sure if I had feelings for him.

371
00:21:14,011 --> 00:21:17,071
I was like, "Do I?" and then, "No."

372
00:21:17,071 --> 00:21:21,341
I thought, "No," as soon as
I got on the escalator.

373
00:21:23,271 --> 00:21:26,801
I was like, "I can't get excited."

374
00:21:26,801 --> 00:21:29,051
[Tap, tap]

375
00:21:29,051 --> 00:21:32,681
I thought I could have a hard time later.

376
00:21:32,681 --> 00:21:34,551
What did you do?

377
00:21:35,821 --> 00:21:37,701
You two.

378
00:21:37,701 --> 00:21:39,491
An izakaya?

379
00:21:39,491 --> 00:21:41,301
Do you know a good sashimi place?

380
00:21:41,301 --> 00:21:44,401
I know one around my work.

381
00:21:45,511 --> 00:21:49,551
I realized what it's like to be bothered.

382
00:21:49,551 --> 00:21:53,441
[The more she suppressed her
feelings, the more they grew]

383
00:21:54,501 --> 00:21:57,951
[Feeling conflicted]

384
00:21:58,431 --> 00:22:00,001
What do we do?

385
00:22:00,001 --> 00:22:03,551
[Heading to work alone]

386
00:22:04,341 --> 00:22:05,531
[Turning around]

387
00:22:07,381 --> 00:22:11,771
You should start the laundry and get some sleep.

388
00:22:13,961 --> 00:22:21,481
Why couldn't I sleep all of a sudden?

389
00:22:24,451 --> 00:22:29,971
[She felt extra conflicted last night]

390
00:22:30,451 --> 00:22:32,041
[Water splashed on her pants]

391
00:22:32,041 --> 00:22:33,471
- What?
- Seriously.

392
00:22:33,471 --> 00:22:35,341
My look is complete.

393
00:22:37,251 --> 00:22:39,841
You look cool. Seriously.

394
00:22:39,841 --> 00:22:42,931
- Doesn't look like I messed up, right?
- No.

395
00:22:43,801 --> 00:22:45,521
Seriously.

396
00:22:47,721 --> 00:22:50,721
- Will you be home after you get back?
- Yes.

397
00:22:50,721 --> 00:22:54,851
Should I pick up something? Anything you want?

398
00:22:56,381 --> 00:22:57,821
Careful.

399
00:22:57,821 --> 00:23:00,011
There's a car behind us.

400
00:23:00,011 --> 00:23:01,921
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are leaving together]

401
00:23:04,941 --> 00:23:07,731
- It's too cold, isn't it?
- Yes.

402
00:23:07,731 --> 00:23:09,661
I'll get the heat going.

403
00:23:09,661 --> 00:23:12,291
[Turning it up]

404
00:23:16,641 --> 00:23:20,901
[Blasting the heater]

405
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:25,821
- It doesn't take that long.
- My goodness.

406
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:28,171
I mean...

407
00:23:28,171 --> 00:23:30,581
Drive me to school, then.

408
00:23:30,581 --> 00:23:34,711
You want me to drive you to school? I can do it.

409
00:23:34,711 --> 00:23:36,691
I can skip work.

410
00:23:36,691 --> 00:23:38,321
[Hehe]

411
00:23:42,461 --> 00:23:45,721
- I'll try not to make you carsick.
- Okay.

412
00:23:53,091 --> 00:23:54,861
So warm.

413
00:23:54,861 --> 00:23:57,361
- You feel okay?
- Yes.

414
00:23:58,221 --> 00:24:00,261
I'm having a warm commute, thanks to you.

415
00:24:00,261 --> 00:24:02,941
[Hehe]

416
00:24:05,321 --> 00:24:07,971
[Musical banner]

417
00:24:07,971 --> 00:24:10,051
- Oh!
- That?

418
00:24:10,051 --> 00:24:12,411
"Dreamland of Peach Blossoms."
I told you about it.

419
00:24:12,411 --> 00:24:15,611
It's happening at the National Theater now.

420
00:24:15,611 --> 00:24:18,051
Right, it's right here.

421
00:24:21,801 --> 00:24:23,891
Want to go see a movie this week?

422
00:24:23,891 --> 00:24:26,491
This week? Really?

423
00:24:29,361 --> 00:24:31,911
- "Once We Were Us."
- After work?

424
00:24:31,911 --> 00:24:34,771
- We can go after work, too.
- When else?

425
00:24:35,671 --> 00:24:36,981
When else, then?

426
00:24:36,981 --> 00:24:39,661
We can go on the weekend, too.

427
00:24:39,661 --> 00:24:43,271
He has strong feelings for Yu Gyeong, too.

428
00:24:45,541 --> 00:24:49,121
Sounds good. I'll check if it's still playing.

429
00:24:50,941 --> 00:24:52,541
[Glancing]

430
00:24:52,541 --> 00:24:53,891
Let me see.

431
00:24:53,891 --> 00:24:56,321
I wonder how long it's playing.

432
00:24:59,611 --> 00:25:03,021
[Keeps replaying the moment he asked her out]

433
00:25:04,621 --> 00:25:05,931
[Glancing]

434
00:25:06,651 --> 00:25:08,771
Where is it?

435
00:25:08,771 --> 00:25:14,081
[Does he really have feelings for me?]

436
00:25:14,951 --> 00:25:17,621
- Aigoo.
- What do we do?

437
00:25:17,621 --> 00:25:21,471
We can find a theater that plays it.

438
00:25:23,691 --> 00:25:28,071
[Feeling more suspicious than happy]

439
00:25:40,061 --> 00:25:42,321
What do I do when I get there?

440
00:25:43,561 --> 00:25:46,921
Is there a store near the school? Daiso?

441
00:25:46,921 --> 00:25:48,831
Right. I should get one.

442
00:25:48,831 --> 00:25:51,991
My old headphones are from Daiso, too.

443
00:25:51,991 --> 00:25:55,041
- When you're at Daiso...
- You want a pan?

444
00:25:55,041 --> 00:25:57,421
It's not a nonstick pan.

445
00:25:57,421 --> 00:25:59,871
You're pulling off the hard task.

446
00:25:59,871 --> 00:26:01,551
I have to.

447
00:26:01,551 --> 00:26:03,741
Are the Daiso pans good enough?

448
00:26:03,741 --> 00:26:06,121
- They're nice.
- Really?

449
00:26:06,121 --> 00:26:08,571
It's nice when it's still new.

450
00:26:08,571 --> 00:26:10,591
Eggs don't stick, either.

451
00:26:10,591 --> 00:26:13,261
- Do I get a pan...
- On the way to school?

452
00:26:13,261 --> 00:26:15,481
Do I carry it around?

453
00:26:15,481 --> 00:26:17,051
[Cracking up]

454
00:26:17,051 --> 00:26:20,751
[They're upbeat again]

455
00:26:22,071 --> 00:26:24,771
Oh, by the way...

456
00:26:24,771 --> 00:26:29,711
we should leave much earlier
if we're driving together.

457
00:26:31,791 --> 00:26:36,611
I really hate being late.

458
00:26:36,611 --> 00:26:40,281
- Me being late to work?
- No, no.

459
00:26:43,641 --> 00:26:46,241
I hate being late myself.

460
00:26:51,411 --> 00:26:56,811
- I wouldn't feel good if you're late, too.
- Goodness.

461
00:26:56,811 --> 00:26:57,831
[Smiling]

462
00:26:57,831 --> 00:27:00,581
[Earlier]

463
00:27:00,581 --> 00:27:03,251
[Wu Yeol wants to drive her further]

464
00:27:03,251 --> 00:27:06,131
I can go this way and that way.

465
00:27:11,441 --> 00:27:14,471
Gosh, I hate it.

466
00:27:14,471 --> 00:27:16,941
- Being late?
- Yes.

467
00:27:18,391 --> 00:27:20,801
It's not even school.

468
00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:28,761
You don't have to worry so much.

469
00:27:31,361 --> 00:27:36,481
I would've said I can't if I couldn't.

470
00:27:36,481 --> 00:27:39,441
I wouldn't have offered you a ride.

471
00:27:39,441 --> 00:27:42,801
I did because I have an idea, too.

472
00:27:42,801 --> 00:27:44,841
Got it.

473
00:27:48,891 --> 00:27:51,601
Thank you.

474
00:27:51,601 --> 00:27:53,731
[Smiling]

475
00:27:56,061 --> 00:27:58,791
What should I have for lunch today?

476
00:27:58,791 --> 00:28:01,601
Rice. Rice bowl.

477
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:06,731
- Cloud egg bowl.
- Cloud egg bowl?

478
00:28:06,731 --> 00:28:08,691
What's that?

479
00:28:08,691 --> 00:28:12,611
- The eggs on top are...
- They look like clouds?

480
00:28:12,611 --> 00:28:14,781
- With a twist in the middle.
- I got it.

481
00:28:14,781 --> 00:28:16,871
- Like an omelet?
- Yes.

482
00:28:16,871 --> 00:28:18,461
It's good.

483
00:28:18,461 --> 00:28:19,611
[Smiling]

484
00:28:20,471 --> 00:28:21,681
[Punch]

485
00:28:21,681 --> 00:28:23,981
[Letting aggression out]

486
00:28:25,321 --> 00:28:28,381
Will there be more good movies?

487
00:28:28,381 --> 00:28:32,541
"Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind"
is playing again.

488
00:28:38,831 --> 00:28:42,081
I want to see that movie.

489
00:28:42,081 --> 00:28:44,271
"Once We Were Us"?

490
00:28:46,561 --> 00:28:48,421
- Wow.
- We're here.

491
00:28:48,421 --> 00:28:51,641
Here's the Exit No. 2.

492
00:28:51,641 --> 00:28:54,701
Thank you so, so much.

493
00:28:55,621 --> 00:28:58,601
Drive carefully.

494
00:29:01,241 --> 00:29:04,491
- Bye.
- See you in the evening.

495
00:29:08,271 --> 00:29:09,291
[Leaning]

496
00:29:12,301 --> 00:29:13,721
I'll go.

497
00:29:21,341 --> 00:29:25,071
- So pretty.
- She's extra pretty today.

498
00:29:25,071 --> 00:29:29,471
[How sincere was he when he talked to her?]

499
00:29:30,031 --> 00:29:34,491
Is there a place you wanted to go to for the date?

500
00:29:35,761 --> 00:29:42,591
I just thought we'd be eating and drinking coffee.

501
00:29:42,591 --> 00:29:46,861
There's a movie I've wanted to watch.

502
00:29:46,861 --> 00:29:49,251
Do you watch movies?

503
00:29:49,251 --> 00:29:50,501
Of course.

504
00:29:50,501 --> 00:29:52,651
- What was that one called?
- "Once We Were Us"?

505
00:29:52,651 --> 00:29:55,461
- I want to watch it.
- Yes, I want to, too.

506
00:29:55,461 --> 00:29:57,211
You haven't seen it yet?

507
00:29:58,201 --> 00:30:00,411
I want to see a movie, but...

508
00:30:02,941 --> 00:30:05,761
I wasn't sure if we could.

509
00:30:06,671 --> 00:30:10,061
- Can we watch a movie?
- I wasn't so sure.

510
00:30:10,061 --> 00:30:12,611
Do you like popcorn? I think you do.

511
00:30:12,611 --> 00:30:14,211
Of course, I do.

512
00:30:14,211 --> 00:30:15,811
[Fidgeting]

513
00:30:15,811 --> 00:30:17,401
[Uneasy]

514
00:30:20,311 --> 00:30:21,931
It'd be fun to see a movie.

515
00:30:21,931 --> 00:30:25,101
I always watch movies alone. I haven't really...

516
00:30:25,101 --> 00:30:28,071
[He can't control his legs]

517
00:30:28,071 --> 00:30:29,641
[Lips drying]

518
00:30:30,781 --> 00:30:34,771
I keep hearing about how good it is.

519
00:30:34,771 --> 00:30:39,401
"Once We Were Us"? It sounded good.

520
00:30:39,401 --> 00:30:42,441
I've been wanting to see it,
but I didn't have the time.

521
00:30:42,441 --> 00:30:45,381
I had no one to watch it with.

522
00:30:45,381 --> 00:30:48,211
"Once We Were Us"? Shall we go see it?

523
00:30:48,211 --> 00:30:50,551
- Sounds good.
- "Zootopia," too?

524
00:30:50,551 --> 00:30:54,171
[They promised to see a movie on the last date]

525
00:30:54,171 --> 00:30:56,081
Daebak.

526
00:31:00,401 --> 00:31:01,711
[Gulp]

527
00:31:02,411 --> 00:31:07,291
[Wu Yeol worked up his courage again]

528
00:31:10,281 --> 00:31:13,741
I think Wu Yeol is devoted to the present.

529
00:31:13,741 --> 00:31:16,141
- Right.
- I've been noticing that.

530
00:31:16,141 --> 00:31:21,731
[A chilly late winter]

531
00:31:23,501 --> 00:31:25,791
Who's this?

532
00:31:25,791 --> 00:31:27,451
Min Ju?

533
00:31:31,651 --> 00:31:35,211
[Kim Min Ju is home, 3 p.m.]

534
00:31:36,871 --> 00:31:40,331
Workout finished. 32 minutes.

535
00:31:40,331 --> 00:31:42,551
[Sigh]

536
00:31:47,121 --> 00:31:51,871
[Kang Yu Gyeong is home, 4:30 p.m.]

537
00:31:53,441 --> 00:31:55,881
- Unni!
- Hey, what took you so long?

538
00:31:55,881 --> 00:31:59,141
- It took me forever to get home.
- Why?

539
00:31:59,141 --> 00:32:01,581
What did you do today?

540
00:32:01,581 --> 00:32:03,951
Seo Won was supposed to be home today.

541
00:32:03,951 --> 00:32:07,701
I thought I'd hang out with him,
but no one was home.

542
00:32:07,701 --> 00:32:10,891
I decided to go for a walk for an hour.

543
00:32:10,891 --> 00:32:14,411
- I bought a trash can for our room.
- Really?

544
00:32:14,411 --> 00:32:16,631
A trash can and a frying pan.

545
00:32:16,631 --> 00:32:18,471
Why did you get a frying pan?

546
00:32:18,471 --> 00:32:24,391
Wu Yeol said he could make anything
if he had a nonstick pan.

547
00:32:24,391 --> 00:32:26,081
How thoughtful of you.

548
00:32:26,081 --> 00:32:28,951
We drove together, you know.

549
00:32:28,951 --> 00:32:30,931
You're right.

550
00:32:31,871 --> 00:32:33,471
[The Dubai chocolate she got with Wu Yeol]

551
00:32:33,471 --> 00:32:35,311
What? Geez.

552
00:32:36,101 --> 00:32:38,031
I can hear the crunch.

553
00:32:40,431 --> 00:32:45,121
So, did you commute with Wu Yeol today?

554
00:32:45,121 --> 00:32:48,621
- He asked me out for a movie.
- What? A movie?

555
00:32:48,621 --> 00:32:51,761
- This week.
- Is he crazy?

556
00:32:51,761 --> 00:32:53,821
So?

557
00:32:53,821 --> 00:32:55,641
I said yes.

558
00:32:57,401 --> 00:33:01,561
- My gosh.
- I don't know what to think.

559
00:33:06,861 --> 00:33:08,361
I'm cold.

560
00:33:09,281 --> 00:33:11,991
Wu Yeol sure is quick.

561
00:33:11,991 --> 00:33:14,601
What do you mean? In what way?

562
00:33:14,601 --> 00:33:19,421
He's quick to ask someone he likes out.

563
00:33:19,421 --> 00:33:27,321
Of course, he's expressing his feelings. He is.

564
00:33:27,321 --> 00:33:29,081
But why...

565
00:33:31,691 --> 00:33:34,101
Why does it not feel that way?

566
00:33:34,101 --> 00:33:36,071
Want to go see a movie this week?

567
00:33:36,071 --> 00:33:37,691
We can go after work, too.

568
00:33:37,691 --> 00:33:41,811
I was like, "Okay. Sure. Let's."

569
00:33:43,051 --> 00:33:45,011
Do you think he wasn't sincere?

570
00:33:45,011 --> 00:33:47,001
It felt like he was just saying that.

571
00:33:47,001 --> 00:33:48,921
She keeps doubting.

572
00:33:49,921 --> 00:33:54,681
My favorite place is a theater.

573
00:33:54,681 --> 00:33:57,581
I like movie theaters.

574
00:33:57,581 --> 00:34:00,471
I like performance theaters, too.

575
00:34:00,471 --> 00:34:03,721
I barely saw any musicals.

576
00:34:03,721 --> 00:34:07,921
- I believe you.
- Want to educate me on that, too?

577
00:34:07,921 --> 00:34:09,731
Let's go.

578
00:34:09,731 --> 00:34:13,401
We'll see a movie and a musical this weekend.

579
00:34:13,401 --> 00:34:15,341
There are many things to do.

580
00:34:15,341 --> 00:34:16,851
We'll be too busy.

581
00:34:16,851 --> 00:34:19,671
I think it's because of how I feel.

582
00:34:19,671 --> 00:34:22,291
I feel like I'm too biased right now.

583
00:34:22,291 --> 00:34:24,441
Why would you say that?

584
00:34:24,441 --> 00:34:26,661
I don't know.

585
00:34:26,661 --> 00:34:29,401
You're doubting everyone, right?

586
00:34:29,401 --> 00:34:37,431
[Revisiting the moments]

587
00:34:39,421 --> 00:34:43,251
I really... I don't know.

588
00:34:43,251 --> 00:34:45,141
[She can't figure out how she feels]

589
00:34:45,141 --> 00:34:47,121
Oh, no...

590
00:34:47,971 --> 00:34:53,461
[How do you fill the emptiness in your heart?]

591
00:34:53,461 --> 00:34:56,571
- I think I'd feel the same, too.
- Right.

592
00:34:56,571 --> 00:34:58,871
She had feelings for him and

593
00:34:58,871 --> 00:35:02,581
she was sure that he had been
texting her every day.

594
00:35:02,581 --> 00:35:06,621
When she figured out why
he's been acting that way,

595
00:35:06,621 --> 00:35:11,821
she must've had a flashback
of the past and was in shock.

596
00:35:11,821 --> 00:35:13,121
She's like, "I was wrong."

597
00:35:13,121 --> 00:35:16,011
I know he asked her out so casually just now.

598
00:35:16,011 --> 00:35:19,601
But even if he sounded sincere,
she'd still be like,

599
00:35:19,601 --> 00:35:24,221
"He didn't mean it." That's how
you feel when you like him a lot.

600
00:35:24,221 --> 00:35:26,331
- You get anxious.
- You do.

601
00:35:26,331 --> 00:35:28,351
Right, right.

602
00:35:30,291 --> 00:35:32,051
Are you going to cook today?

603
00:35:32,051 --> 00:35:34,571
I think I should. Everyone comes home late.

604
00:35:34,571 --> 00:35:35,931
What will you make?

605
00:35:35,931 --> 00:35:37,991
- Beef radish soup.
- I'd love that.

606
00:35:37,991 --> 00:35:39,161
Sounds good, right?

607
00:35:39,161 --> 00:35:41,591
- Is someone cooking today?
- The three of us.

608
00:35:41,591 --> 00:35:43,681
What? Says who?

609
00:35:43,681 --> 00:35:47,531
- It won't be cold, right?
- I'm sure it is. Is that what you're wearing?

610
00:35:47,531 --> 00:35:51,371
Yes. It's a short walk. Seven minutes?

611
00:35:51,371 --> 00:35:53,631
You can't run, okay?

612
00:35:53,631 --> 00:35:54,851
Let's go.

613
00:35:54,851 --> 00:35:56,901
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

614
00:35:56,901 --> 00:35:59,071
- This is it.
- Yes.

615
00:35:59,071 --> 00:36:01,571
Min Ju wanted sweet potatoes.

616
00:36:01,571 --> 00:36:05,001
- Should we bring some?
- Sounds good. I love them, too.

617
00:36:05,001 --> 00:36:06,931
Hello.

618
00:36:09,781 --> 00:36:11,541
Oh, no!

619
00:36:13,071 --> 00:36:15,301
The radish is rolling.

620
00:36:16,221 --> 00:36:17,721
[You laugh at everything at their age]

621
00:36:17,721 --> 00:36:19,481
They're cute.

622
00:36:21,421 --> 00:36:25,071
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

623
00:36:25,071 --> 00:36:28,331
- Thank you. Take care.
- Thank you.

624
00:36:29,161 --> 00:36:34,651
- Wow, we're rich.
- Bungeoppang is a must in winter.

625
00:36:35,481 --> 00:36:37,481
[Peeping]

626
00:36:39,101 --> 00:36:42,891
Aigoo, she feels guilty.

627
00:36:42,891 --> 00:36:44,821
[Tiptoing]

628
00:36:48,151 --> 00:36:50,711
- You're back.
- Yes.

629
00:36:50,711 --> 00:36:54,051
We're cooking now, right?

630
00:36:54,051 --> 00:36:57,811
You can rest, Unni. It's totally fine.

631
00:36:59,921 --> 00:37:02,661
I'll let you know when it's ready.

632
00:37:02,661 --> 00:37:05,871
I'll let you know when it's ready.

633
00:37:05,871 --> 00:37:07,761
- Rest, then.
- Okay.

634
00:37:07,761 --> 00:37:10,361
She must be sick.

635
00:37:10,361 --> 00:37:12,281
Come on. Where's Seong Min?

636
00:37:12,281 --> 00:37:14,051
He should come and care for her.

637
00:37:14,051 --> 00:37:16,131
Doctor.

638
00:37:19,511 --> 00:37:22,631
How much do we have left after grocery shopping?

639
00:37:27,091 --> 00:37:29,051
Interest.

640
00:37:29,051 --> 00:37:31,771
Daebak. We get cash back.

641
00:37:31,771 --> 00:37:33,521
So cool.

642
00:37:36,451 --> 00:37:38,431
You like it?

643
00:37:38,431 --> 00:37:40,831
I'm so proud of myself.

644
00:37:40,831 --> 00:37:43,371
[Starting to cook]

645
00:37:43,371 --> 00:37:46,811
- You're good.
- It's too small.

646
00:37:46,811 --> 00:37:49,471
[Improving cooking skills]

647
00:37:49,471 --> 00:37:51,251
You're way better than me.

648
00:37:52,871 --> 00:37:55,231
Seo Won wanted this on Episode 1.

649
00:37:55,231 --> 00:37:57,831
- Going in now?
- Starting to cook.

650
00:37:57,831 --> 00:38:03,201
Stir-fry the beef in sesame oil and
cooking oil, then add the radish.

651
00:38:03,201 --> 00:38:06,461
Add water and adjust the
seasoning. So simple, right?

652
00:38:06,461 --> 00:38:07,661
He learned on YouTube.

653
00:38:07,661 --> 00:38:09,981
Bring it to a boil. We're done.

654
00:38:09,981 --> 00:38:11,431
Good.

655
00:38:11,431 --> 00:38:12,961
Try it.

656
00:38:12,961 --> 00:38:16,201
It could be hot. Spit it out if it is.

657
00:38:16,201 --> 00:38:17,831
[Mmm!]

658
00:38:17,831 --> 00:38:19,931
It tastes familiar, right?

659
00:38:19,931 --> 00:38:22,651
We just need the legendary omelet.

660
00:38:23,601 --> 00:38:27,071
- The color looks great.
- Daebak. Game over.

661
00:38:27,071 --> 00:38:30,991
When the eggs solidify, fold like this.

662
00:38:30,991 --> 00:38:34,181
[Skillfully making an omelet]

663
00:38:37,001 --> 00:38:39,201
[Focused]

664
00:38:40,681 --> 00:38:42,431
[Skillful]

665
00:38:42,431 --> 00:38:44,691
Want to see something amazing?

666
00:38:44,691 --> 00:38:47,941
- Did you see this?
- Don't be shocked. I mean it.

667
00:38:47,941 --> 00:38:50,291
- Should I show it now?
- Go ahead.

668
00:38:50,291 --> 00:38:51,821
Hold on. Hold on.

669
00:38:51,821 --> 00:38:54,811
- Hey, that's not it.
- Okay, okay.

670
00:38:55,701 --> 00:38:57,231
One, two, three.

671
00:38:57,231 --> 00:38:58,931
- Ta-da!
- Who made this?

672
00:38:58,931 --> 00:39:02,091
- How did you shape it like this?
- That was a real reaction.

673
00:39:02,091 --> 00:39:05,071
- That was too fake.
- How did you do it?

674
00:39:05,071 --> 00:39:07,841
You reacted way too fast.

675
00:39:07,841 --> 00:39:10,241
"How did you do it?" How did you shape it?

676
00:39:10,241 --> 00:39:13,151
I believed him. I thought he meant it.

677
00:39:13,151 --> 00:39:15,881
I thought it was from a store.

678
00:39:15,881 --> 00:39:17,901
I made it.

679
00:39:20,401 --> 00:39:22,301
[Looking around]

680
00:39:23,821 --> 00:39:26,921
Unni, are you awake?

681
00:39:27,751 --> 00:39:29,951
[Min Ju is still not feeling well]

682
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:32,231
Yu Gyeong is worried.

683
00:39:33,351 --> 00:39:35,691
I'll let you rest more.

684
00:39:35,691 --> 00:39:38,691
She really must be sick.

685
00:39:38,691 --> 00:39:40,851
Good thing I didn't eat.

686
00:39:40,851 --> 00:39:43,251
Min Ju doesn't think she can eat now.

687
00:39:43,251 --> 00:39:45,961
- Is she very sick?
- Yes, she's been feeling ill.

688
00:39:45,961 --> 00:39:48,201
- All of a sudden?
- Has she seen a doctor?

689
00:39:48,201 --> 00:39:49,841
I don't think she has.

690
00:39:49,841 --> 00:39:51,901
If she can't eat, it must be serious.

691
00:39:51,901 --> 00:39:53,601
She can't even eat.

692
00:39:53,601 --> 00:39:57,461
Shouldn't she go to a hospital and get an IV?

693
00:39:57,461 --> 00:39:59,871
She only took medicine.

694
00:40:01,071 --> 00:40:04,421
[It's past 10, but Wu Yeol and
Gyu Ri aren't home yet]

695
00:40:04,421 --> 00:40:07,671
They're on a date. Seriously.
Only those two aren't here.

696
00:40:07,671 --> 00:40:10,011
- I feel hurt.
- I do, too.

697
00:40:10,011 --> 00:40:12,771
Yu Gyeong is bothered by that.

698
00:40:12,771 --> 00:40:14,861
Seo Won must be waiting for Gyu Ri, too.

699
00:40:14,861 --> 00:40:17,441
They'll probably come home separately.

700
00:40:18,471 --> 00:40:20,611
- They'll probably come together.
- They might.

701
00:40:20,611 --> 00:40:23,381
I won't ask any questions.

702
00:40:23,381 --> 00:40:25,871
[Refusing to talk to them]

703
00:40:25,871 --> 00:40:28,461
[It's getting late]

704
00:40:28,461 --> 00:40:30,811
She can't laugh.

705
00:40:32,251 --> 00:40:34,771
We shouldn't be waiting this late.

706
00:40:34,771 --> 00:40:37,091
I want to wait. I want to feed them.

707
00:40:37,091 --> 00:40:39,181
What do we do?

708
00:40:40,261 --> 00:40:42,341
You saw that face, right?

709
00:40:42,341 --> 00:40:45,531
When they said, "Aren't they on a date?"
her face froze.

710
00:40:45,531 --> 00:40:47,941
She was smiling with her mouth,
but not with her eyes.

711
00:40:47,941 --> 00:40:49,251
- Right.
- She's so transparent.

712
00:40:49,251 --> 00:40:51,591
It had to be those two who were missing.

713
00:40:51,591 --> 00:40:55,021
The ones who waited for them cooked for them.

714
00:40:55,021 --> 00:40:58,581
It's so sad hearing it like that. So devastating.

715
00:40:58,581 --> 00:41:02,341
But things are still working out for Yu Gyeong.

716
00:41:02,341 --> 00:41:04,501
- They have a movie date, too.
- Right, right.

717
00:41:04,501 --> 00:41:08,051
They talked about carpooling again, too.

718
00:41:08,051 --> 00:41:12,931
What I'm realizing is that doubt seems

719
00:41:12,931 --> 00:41:17,121
insignificant, but it can be powerful.

720
00:41:17,121 --> 00:41:19,331
Since she has a bit of a doubt,

721
00:41:19,331 --> 00:41:24,721
she's sure they're together even though
that might not be the case.

722
00:41:24,721 --> 00:41:30,631
Because of that, things will get
awkward the next time they meet.

723
00:41:30,631 --> 00:41:33,271
Leaning the pieces would look better.

724
00:41:33,271 --> 00:41:35,661
Wow, what a presentation.

725
00:41:35,661 --> 00:41:37,321
He really did a good job.

726
00:41:37,321 --> 00:41:39,981
- It's getting weird.
- It's kind of... Hold on. Hold on.

727
00:41:39,981 --> 00:41:43,121
- It looked better before.
- It's gradually getting...

728
00:41:43,881 --> 00:41:45,891
Thank you.

729
00:41:45,891 --> 00:41:47,051
I'm okay.

730
00:41:47,051 --> 00:41:50,491
[They worked hard on the omelet]

731
00:41:50,491 --> 00:41:52,621
[Staring]

732
00:41:52,621 --> 00:41:55,501
Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

733
00:41:55,501 --> 00:41:58,211
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you.

734
00:42:01,861 --> 00:42:04,201
What's with you? Stop lying.

735
00:42:04,201 --> 00:42:05,961
Seriously.

736
00:42:05,961 --> 00:42:09,301
- You're forcing it again.
- You're doing it too much.

737
00:42:09,301 --> 00:42:12,721
Seriously, the soup didn't
even go inside his mouth.

738
00:42:12,721 --> 00:42:15,881
- But he reacted.
- But it's good.

739
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:17,841
- It's so good.
- It is.

740
00:42:17,841 --> 00:42:22,521
You're saying the same thing,
but just a beat later.

741
00:42:22,521 --> 00:42:23,991
It's good. It's good.

742
00:42:23,991 --> 00:42:26,041
Who's the cook?

743
00:42:27,151 --> 00:42:28,571
[Smiling]

744
00:42:28,571 --> 00:42:31,141
- Seong Min is too excited.
- He really is.

745
00:42:31,141 --> 00:42:34,131
Min Ju's stomach is churning right now.

746
00:42:34,131 --> 00:42:36,971
I know. I'm sure she can hear all this.

747
00:42:36,971 --> 00:42:39,311
Did you chop all the veggies, too?

748
00:42:39,311 --> 00:42:40,661
Yes. Like this.

749
00:42:40,661 --> 00:42:43,641
Seriously. We used the julienne knife.

750
00:42:43,641 --> 00:42:45,161
The onion, too.

751
00:42:45,161 --> 00:42:47,081
- Good job.
- It was minced so well.

752
00:42:47,081 --> 00:42:50,521
- I thought you had a chopper.
- She cut with a knife like this.

753
00:42:50,521 --> 00:42:52,371
Wow.

754
00:42:53,041 --> 00:42:57,071
[She was clumsy, but she worked hard]

755
00:42:57,071 --> 00:42:58,651
[Careful]

756
00:43:01,521 --> 00:43:05,621
[Where's the man she bought the pan for?]

757
00:43:12,191 --> 00:43:13,911
I'm sad that not everyone is here.

758
00:43:13,911 --> 00:43:17,991
I know. It's so delicious.

759
00:43:17,991 --> 00:43:20,831
- They aren't coming.
- She's bothered.

760
00:43:20,831 --> 00:43:24,381
It's getting too late. He was
supposed to be done at seven.

761
00:43:24,381 --> 00:43:26,441
[Bothered]

762
00:43:26,441 --> 00:43:29,841
They're on a date. Seriously.
Only those two aren't here.

763
00:43:29,841 --> 00:43:31,931
They'll probably come home separately.

764
00:43:31,931 --> 00:43:34,011
- They'll probably come together.
- They might.

765
00:43:34,011 --> 00:43:36,551
I won't ask any questions.

766
00:43:41,411 --> 00:43:43,431
[The dinner is coming to an end]

767
00:43:43,431 --> 00:43:45,601
She's anxious. My gosh.

768
00:43:45,601 --> 00:43:48,231
[The waiting continues]

769
00:43:52,211 --> 00:43:57,281
[Is Wu Yeol coming home with someone?]

770
00:44:01,131 --> 00:44:02,911
Would you be able to eat?

771
00:44:02,911 --> 00:44:05,261
You haven't eaten yet?

772
00:44:05,261 --> 00:44:09,481
The two aren't here yet. Wu Yeol and Gyu Ri.

773
00:44:09,481 --> 00:44:12,611
- Are they together?
- Are they?

774
00:44:12,611 --> 00:44:14,551
That's a meaningful question.

775
00:44:14,551 --> 00:44:17,611
I want to finish the omelet.

776
00:44:17,611 --> 00:44:20,191
[Footsteps are approaching]

777
00:44:22,621 --> 00:44:26,501
- Are they coming home together?
- Please, please.

778
00:44:26,501 --> 00:44:28,041
Oh?

779
00:44:32,431 --> 00:44:34,721
[Gyu Ri shows up first]

780
00:44:35,721 --> 00:44:39,271
Gyu Ri, come and eat. We just started eating.

781
00:44:39,271 --> 00:44:41,681
- She's alone. She's alone.
- My gosh.

782
00:44:41,681 --> 00:44:44,441
- Did you eat?
- You're eating now?

783
00:44:44,441 --> 00:44:46,821
Have you eaten?

784
00:44:46,821 --> 00:44:48,911
She's smiling.

785
00:44:48,911 --> 00:44:50,491
We've been waiting for you.

786
00:44:50,491 --> 00:44:52,791
Thank you.

787
00:44:52,791 --> 00:44:55,361
We started five minutes ago. Join us.

788
00:44:55,361 --> 00:44:57,031
Really? What a relief.

789
00:44:57,031 --> 00:44:59,661
Am I sitting in the middle?

790
00:45:00,641 --> 00:45:02,451
- The star.
- I'll sit in the middle.

791
00:45:02,451 --> 00:45:05,721
- He's fixing his shirt and bangs.
- So cute.

792
00:45:05,721 --> 00:45:08,211
We've been waiting for you.

793
00:45:08,211 --> 00:45:10,711
- I'm sorry.
- No, it's okay.

794
00:45:10,711 --> 00:45:14,241
Hold on. I'll be right back. Keep eating.

795
00:45:14,241 --> 00:45:16,541
Min Ju is sleeping.

796
00:45:16,541 --> 00:45:19,321
Okay. Thank you.

797
00:45:20,341 --> 00:45:22,541
He's staring at her.

798
00:45:28,171 --> 00:45:29,171
[Grin]

799
00:45:29,171 --> 00:45:32,081
It's cute how transparent she is.

800
00:45:34,781 --> 00:45:39,241
This is the tastiest meal I've had here.

801
00:45:39,241 --> 00:45:40,641
She's suddenly enjoying it?

802
00:45:40,641 --> 00:45:42,081
[Only three pieces of omelet are left]

803
00:45:42,951 --> 00:45:45,181
We should give her some omelet.

804
00:45:45,181 --> 00:45:48,281
- You're right.
- She should taste it.

805
00:45:48,281 --> 00:45:49,651
Do we stop now?

806
00:45:49,651 --> 00:45:53,371
- We should stop.
- He says to stop eating.

807
00:45:54,701 --> 00:45:56,461
[One shot]

808
00:45:56,461 --> 00:45:59,241
We should stay while Gyu Ri eats.

809
00:45:59,241 --> 00:46:01,761
I should slow down.

810
00:46:01,761 --> 00:46:05,801
He wants them to stay. That's it.

811
00:46:05,801 --> 00:46:09,041
- He wants to eat with her.
- He's cool.

812
00:46:11,711 --> 00:46:15,091
[Serving soup for Gyu Ri]

813
00:46:15,711 --> 00:46:17,151
[Worried]

814
00:46:17,151 --> 00:46:19,251
- Is that the rest of it?
- No.

815
00:46:19,251 --> 00:46:20,741
There's plenty left.

816
00:46:20,741 --> 00:46:24,181
She's worried there's nothing left for Wu Yeol.

817
00:46:28,261 --> 00:46:30,181
I'm sorry.

818
00:46:32,111 --> 00:46:34,611
Hold on. I'll be right in the middle.

819
00:46:34,611 --> 00:46:36,671
Guess who cooked this meal?

820
00:46:37,631 --> 00:46:39,751
He's trying to impress her.

821
00:46:39,751 --> 00:46:41,231
Yu Gyeong?

822
00:46:42,331 --> 00:46:43,771
There's one more person.

823
00:46:43,771 --> 00:46:46,481
- He wants to tell her.
- Guess based on the taste.

824
00:46:46,481 --> 00:46:48,221
Based on the taste?

825
00:46:48,221 --> 00:46:50,951
We don't know each other that well.

826
00:46:50,951 --> 00:46:54,791
- So cute.
- His cheekbones are all the way up.

827
00:46:54,791 --> 00:46:56,981
Why is it so good?

828
00:46:56,981 --> 00:46:59,151
- So good.
- Right? Oops.

829
00:46:59,151 --> 00:47:01,521
[Seo Won doesn't want to hide]

830
00:47:02,341 --> 00:47:06,451
It was you. You're such a good cook.

831
00:47:06,451 --> 00:47:08,421
He must be so happy.

832
00:47:08,421 --> 00:47:11,931
- It turned out well.
- You have a talent.

833
00:47:11,931 --> 00:47:14,001
[Relieved]

834
00:47:14,671 --> 00:47:17,371
- Thank you for the meal.
- This is my second serving.

835
00:47:17,371 --> 00:47:19,371
I had to prove that it's tasty.

836
00:47:19,371 --> 00:47:21,451
Seriously, it's good.

837
00:47:21,451 --> 00:47:25,681
I want you to make this again.
I mean it. Could you?

838
00:47:28,191 --> 00:47:30,051
What did you do?

839
00:47:31,091 --> 00:47:33,521
- Today.
- Today?

840
00:47:34,641 --> 00:47:37,331
[Smiling]

841
00:47:38,151 --> 00:47:39,771
- Are you done?
- Yes.

842
00:47:39,771 --> 00:47:42,851
Should we snack on something in the living room?

843
00:47:46,211 --> 00:47:47,651
- Did you have a good day?
- Yes.

844
00:47:47,651 --> 00:47:49,491
- Wow.
- My gosh.

845
00:47:49,491 --> 00:47:51,611
What time do you leave tomorrow?

846
00:47:51,611 --> 00:47:53,511
5:30?

847
00:47:53,511 --> 00:47:55,661
I'm waking up at 5:30.

848
00:47:55,661 --> 00:47:59,991
- I should high-five everyone.
- I know.

849
00:48:01,621 --> 00:48:05,221
- I'll get dinner ready again.
- So sweet!

850
00:48:11,541 --> 00:48:14,411
[Wu Yeol came home looking a bit tired]

851
00:48:17,441 --> 00:48:18,851
What would happen?

852
00:48:18,851 --> 00:48:21,091
[Looking]

853
00:48:25,381 --> 00:48:27,071
Hello.

854
00:48:27,071 --> 00:48:29,461
She's greeting him happily.

855
00:48:29,461 --> 00:48:31,221
Hello?

856
00:48:31,221 --> 00:48:33,951
Sounds like Wu Yeol is home.

857
00:48:33,951 --> 00:48:36,571
- Why are you back so late?
- I'm home.

858
00:48:36,571 --> 00:48:38,511
Tell us now.

859
00:48:38,511 --> 00:48:39,951
Why are you so late?

860
00:48:39,951 --> 00:48:43,081
The look in her eyes is still the same.

861
00:48:43,081 --> 00:48:44,621
I stopped by a pharmacy.

862
00:48:44,621 --> 00:48:45,921
Did you have a lot of work?

863
00:48:45,921 --> 00:48:49,251
[She can't take her eyes off of Wu Yeol]

864
00:48:49,251 --> 00:48:51,131
- For real, huh?
- Have you eaten?

865
00:48:51,131 --> 00:48:53,011
- Have you eaten?
- Yes.

866
00:48:53,011 --> 00:48:55,251
We made a good meal.

867
00:48:55,251 --> 00:48:57,601
I haven't had dinner yet.

868
00:48:57,601 --> 00:49:00,581
Have some. We have leftovers.

869
00:49:00,581 --> 00:49:03,291
He looks a bit tired.

870
00:49:04,881 --> 00:49:07,771
She can't ignore him.

871
00:49:09,551 --> 00:49:14,751
- The vibe totally changed.
- He's a vibe maker.

872
00:49:14,751 --> 00:49:18,321
[Wu Yeol is heading to the kitchen]

873
00:49:19,991 --> 00:49:22,271
- Hello.
- Have you eaten?

874
00:49:22,271 --> 00:49:24,831
- No, I haven't.
- We got food there.

875
00:49:24,831 --> 00:49:27,031
It must be cold.

876
00:49:27,921 --> 00:49:34,221
- Will she heat it up for him?
- I'm thinking of skipping dinner.

877
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:36,861
She worked so hard on it.

878
00:49:36,861 --> 00:49:40,111
- What did you have?
- Beef radish soup.

879
00:49:40,111 --> 00:49:42,861
- Sounds good.
- It was amazing. It's over there.

880
00:49:42,861 --> 00:49:45,091
I have an upset stomach.

881
00:49:45,091 --> 00:49:47,831
Gosh, he was sick.

882
00:49:47,831 --> 00:49:51,081
Why is everyone sick?

883
00:49:51,081 --> 00:49:52,691
I'm sad.

884
00:49:52,691 --> 00:49:55,381
Do we get sick by coming here?

885
00:49:55,381 --> 00:49:57,661
That's likely.

886
00:49:57,661 --> 00:49:59,311
[Glancing]

887
00:49:59,791 --> 00:50:01,471
- It's a little...
- What?

888
00:50:01,471 --> 00:50:05,701
- It looks a bit...
- It's the parsley.

889
00:50:06,631 --> 00:50:08,441
[Staring]

890
00:50:08,991 --> 00:50:12,271
Can I tell you what I just thought of?
We have scallions.

891
00:50:12,271 --> 00:50:16,121
Let's crisp it up in the oven and shatter them.

892
00:50:16,121 --> 00:50:18,481
Just eat outside instead.

893
00:50:18,481 --> 00:50:21,011
- That?
- There's a lot.

894
00:50:22,381 --> 00:50:25,711
I think black pepper would be good.

895
00:50:25,711 --> 00:50:27,751
For this?

896
00:50:27,751 --> 00:50:29,951
Which one?

897
00:50:29,951 --> 00:50:32,611
- One of these?
- We already used this.

898
00:50:32,611 --> 00:50:35,021
We can't go back.

899
00:50:35,021 --> 00:50:37,061
[Zoning out]

900
00:50:38,551 --> 00:50:40,891
[Yum, yum]

901
00:50:40,891 --> 00:50:44,081
[Gyu Ri and Seo Won are the only
ones in the living room]

902
00:50:44,991 --> 00:50:46,661
[Looking]

903
00:50:46,661 --> 00:50:49,341
She's only interested in what's going on there.

904
00:50:49,341 --> 00:50:51,721
You must be tired.

905
00:50:51,721 --> 00:50:53,441
I want to eat quickly.

906
00:50:53,441 --> 00:50:56,241
You want to eat and go to bed, right?

907
00:50:57,821 --> 00:51:01,411
[Seo Won is lost in thought]

908
00:51:01,771 --> 00:51:03,631
5:30.

909
00:51:04,611 --> 00:51:07,861
It's perfect timing.

910
00:51:07,861 --> 00:51:09,771
[Closing eyes]

911
00:51:10,911 --> 00:51:12,491
[Staring]

912
00:51:14,081 --> 00:51:19,631
[What kind of feelings are brewing now?]

913
00:51:24,801 --> 00:51:25,781
[Looking]

914
00:51:29,131 --> 00:51:30,411
[Bothered]

915
00:51:31,071 --> 00:51:33,801
[Wu Yeol is not looking well]

916
00:51:33,801 --> 00:51:35,451
- It's concerning.
- Yes.

917
00:51:35,451 --> 00:51:38,451
He's making her worry.

918
00:51:38,451 --> 00:51:41,151
[A lot of worries tonight]

919
00:51:41,151 --> 00:51:42,701
Is everyone here?

920
00:51:42,701 --> 00:51:47,071
Min Ju has been home all day,

921
00:51:47,071 --> 00:51:49,621
but she's feeling ill.

922
00:51:50,761 --> 00:51:52,821
[Sigh]

923
00:51:54,791 --> 00:51:56,841
[Worried]

924
00:51:59,441 --> 00:52:02,191
- Your eyes are red.
- Are they?

925
00:52:03,081 --> 00:52:04,731
You must be tired.

926
00:52:07,551 --> 00:52:12,641
I had the chills since four today.

927
00:52:12,641 --> 00:52:15,021
I was sweating.

928
00:52:15,021 --> 00:52:19,761
I think I have the flu and enteritis.

929
00:52:19,761 --> 00:52:23,141
Really? You should eat and go to bed.

930
00:52:23,141 --> 00:52:25,011
I'm not going to eat.

931
00:52:27,261 --> 00:52:29,131
No, no...

932
00:52:30,691 --> 00:52:33,151
Gyu Ri is transparent, too.

933
00:52:33,151 --> 00:52:35,011
- What?
- I just got home.

934
00:52:35,011 --> 00:52:37,781
- Where have you been?
- I got off work.

935
00:52:37,781 --> 00:52:40,271
I got back late from work.

936
00:52:40,271 --> 00:52:42,981
You had a date with a game-changer, didn't you?

937
00:52:42,981 --> 00:52:44,871
Yes, I did.

938
00:52:46,021 --> 00:52:48,381
- You have the flu?
- I got enteritis, too.

939
00:52:48,381 --> 00:52:51,491
- Did you go to the hospital?
- Yes, I went to the pharmacy.

940
00:52:51,491 --> 00:52:54,071
- You said he was on a date.
- He's not listening.

941
00:52:54,071 --> 00:52:55,721
He's lying.

942
00:52:56,671 --> 00:53:00,421
- He's lying. Are you lying?
- So funny.

943
00:53:00,421 --> 00:53:04,191
Why are you suddenly sick? Why is everyone sick?

944
00:53:04,191 --> 00:53:07,681
- Since when?
- After I had lunch today.

945
00:53:07,681 --> 00:53:10,231
Really? Is it because you're nervous?

946
00:53:11,231 --> 00:53:13,501
Nervous?

947
00:53:13,501 --> 00:53:14,671
[Ears perked]

948
00:53:14,671 --> 00:53:16,821
Is there a reason to be?

949
00:53:17,881 --> 00:53:19,341
[Mouth twitching]

950
00:53:21,031 --> 00:53:25,001
[Every word is bothering her today]

951
00:53:31,401 --> 00:53:32,351
[Clumsy]

952
00:53:32,351 --> 00:53:34,151
Ring the bell.

953
00:53:39,951 --> 00:53:44,131
He seems older than you.

954
00:53:49,681 --> 00:53:52,701
- Did you get off work late today?
- Yes.

955
00:53:52,701 --> 00:53:55,861
I have to leave at dawn starting tomorrow.

956
00:53:58,431 --> 00:54:00,701
And you come home late?

957
00:54:00,701 --> 00:54:03,441
I'll be off at seven.

958
00:54:04,281 --> 00:54:07,001
- What time do you leave?
- To carpool again?

959
00:54:07,001 --> 00:54:09,091
I have to get up at 5:30.

960
00:54:11,661 --> 00:54:15,691
- You'll be so tired.
- I'm thinking of leaving at 6:30.

961
00:54:15,691 --> 00:54:20,831
You won't be seeing me in the morning anymore.

962
00:54:20,831 --> 00:54:22,441
I know.

963
00:54:23,301 --> 00:54:24,591
Today was the last time.

964
00:54:24,591 --> 00:54:28,001
- That's so cruel.
- That was their last morning.

965
00:54:28,001 --> 00:54:30,211
You need to take care of yourself.

966
00:54:31,041 --> 00:54:33,081
Seo Won is here just in time.

967
00:54:33,991 --> 00:54:39,841
[The time for the two of them ended quickly]

968
00:54:40,391 --> 00:54:42,771
I feel like I'm being judged.

969
00:54:44,461 --> 00:54:46,721
We've done it now.

970
00:54:46,721 --> 00:54:50,761
It was fun. Fine dining is all about the process.

971
00:54:50,761 --> 00:54:53,021
- It was so fun.
- I know.

972
00:54:53,021 --> 00:54:55,661
[Fine dining sweet potatoes are here]

973
00:54:55,661 --> 00:54:58,241
Here's the dish we prepared today.

974
00:54:58,241 --> 00:55:04,921
These are three interpretations
of sweet potatoes grown in Haenam.

975
00:55:04,921 --> 00:55:08,501
- Start from the left.
- The left one is the original.

976
00:55:08,501 --> 00:55:10,951
The natural form matters the most.

977
00:55:10,951 --> 00:55:13,591
It's the best version.

978
00:55:13,591 --> 00:55:16,371
Does that make sense?

979
00:55:16,371 --> 00:55:17,921
Cheese.

980
00:55:17,921 --> 00:55:20,011
Huh?

981
00:55:20,011 --> 00:55:22,591
- Are you okay?
- No.

982
00:55:22,591 --> 00:55:24,551
Look at his face.

983
00:55:24,551 --> 00:55:27,251
Were you at work?

984
00:55:27,251 --> 00:55:28,651
[Staring]

985
00:55:28,651 --> 00:55:30,741
When did you get home?

986
00:55:30,741 --> 00:55:33,181
I came early.

987
00:55:33,181 --> 00:55:36,541
I got out at two. I came home at two.

988
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:40,721
- I spent two hours at a cafe.
- It must bother her so much.

989
00:55:44,861 --> 00:55:46,731
Should we try it?

990
00:55:47,721 --> 00:55:49,311
Eat it in one bite.

991
00:55:49,311 --> 00:55:52,221
- Looks good.
- Wow, look at his face.

992
00:55:52,221 --> 00:55:55,021
The Aussie...

993
00:55:55,021 --> 00:55:57,681
What's this one?

994
00:55:57,681 --> 00:56:00,771
I think this is our masterpiece.

995
00:56:00,771 --> 00:56:02,871
[Bothered]

996
00:56:02,871 --> 00:56:05,051
It's a masterpiece.

997
00:56:05,051 --> 00:56:06,581
- Did you eat?
- No, I didn't.

998
00:56:06,581 --> 00:56:08,621
You didn't?

999
00:56:08,621 --> 00:56:11,621
- What do we do?
- Excuse me.

1000
00:56:12,771 --> 00:56:15,801
Let's drink. Let's all drink.

1001
00:56:16,781 --> 00:56:17,981
He must be going upstairs.

1002
00:56:17,981 --> 00:56:20,451
[Wu Yeol is leaving]

1003
00:56:23,181 --> 00:56:25,171
- Shall we?
- Yes.

1004
00:56:25,171 --> 00:56:27,881
- Cheers.
- Good work today.

1005
00:56:27,881 --> 00:56:30,131
[Having drinks without Wu Yeol]

1006
00:56:33,411 --> 00:56:37,491
[Is it because he's sick?]

1007
00:56:39,071 --> 00:56:40,891
Looks like he's suffering.

1008
00:56:40,891 --> 00:56:45,351
- Why is everyone sick?
- I know.

1009
00:56:45,351 --> 00:56:47,451
They both said they got the chills.

1010
00:56:47,451 --> 00:56:50,191
- Wu Yeol has been sweating since four.
- 4 p.m.?

1011
00:56:50,191 --> 00:56:53,641
That's what he told me earlier.

1012
00:56:54,721 --> 00:56:56,441
[Concerned]

1013
00:56:58,921 --> 00:56:59,731
[Looking]

1014
00:57:05,671 --> 00:57:07,581
[Tossing]

1015
00:57:10,221 --> 00:57:14,151
[Wu Yeol is back on the first floor]

1016
00:57:14,871 --> 00:57:15,771
[Looking]

1017
00:57:16,701 --> 00:57:19,791
Whenever Wu Yeol shows up, she's...

1018
00:57:22,241 --> 00:57:24,501
[Turning]

1019
00:57:25,611 --> 00:57:29,041
- Going over there again?
- What do we do?

1020
00:57:29,041 --> 00:57:31,781
Let's go to bed by one or two tonight.

1021
00:57:31,781 --> 00:57:33,251
You go to bed earlier.

1022
00:57:33,251 --> 00:57:35,551
[Wu Yeol is sitting next to Gyu Ri]

1023
00:57:35,551 --> 00:57:37,951
He had nowhere else to sit.

1024
00:57:39,591 --> 00:57:42,121
It must be because you've been tired.

1025
00:57:42,121 --> 00:57:45,841
- I've been staying up.
- That must've affected a lot.

1026
00:57:45,841 --> 00:57:52,111
[She can't manage her complicated feelings]

1027
00:58:00,001 --> 00:58:02,621
The dinner was delicious tonight.

1028
00:58:02,621 --> 00:58:04,191
The omelet.

1029
00:58:05,171 --> 00:58:07,621
- It must be love-sick.
- I know.

1030
00:58:07,621 --> 00:58:11,941
It doesn't show, but they're having
battles inside right now.

1031
00:58:11,941 --> 00:58:13,801
- That's right.
- Min Ju, too.

1032
00:58:13,801 --> 00:58:15,321
It's making them sick.

1033
00:58:15,321 --> 00:58:20,061
When Wu Yeol came home sick,
the two suddenly got nervous.

1034
00:58:20,061 --> 00:58:22,231
Gyu Ri and Yu Gyeong.

1035
00:58:22,231 --> 00:58:24,451
Wu Yeol did the same thing again at the end.

1036
00:58:24,451 --> 00:58:28,471
He had fun with Yu Gyeong,
but he sat next to Gyu Ri.

1037
00:58:28,471 --> 00:58:32,351
I don't think Yu Gyeong will
text Wu Yeol tonight.

1038
00:58:32,351 --> 00:58:36,241
Yu Gyeong is very pessimistic today.

1039
00:58:36,241 --> 00:58:39,521
Because of that, she can't text him again.

1040
00:58:39,521 --> 00:58:43,531
She stayed up because she's
been mistaken all this time.

1041
00:58:43,531 --> 00:58:46,711
I was shocked that she stayed up all night.

1042
00:58:46,711 --> 00:58:48,631
I didn't know her feelings were that serious.

1043
00:58:48,631 --> 00:58:51,211
I wouldn't be able to text him tonight.

1044
00:58:51,211 --> 00:58:55,221
- She's avoiding Wu Yeol?
- That's more confusing.

1045
00:58:55,221 --> 00:58:58,991
If she doesn't text him to avoid him,

1046
00:58:58,991 --> 00:59:02,441
there will be misunderstandings.
Will she risk that?

1047
00:59:02,441 --> 00:59:04,641
I'm not sure. That's what I just thought.

1048
00:59:04,641 --> 00:59:07,751
Shouldn't they express
their feelings clearly now?

1049
00:59:07,751 --> 00:59:09,831
I think she'll text Wu Yeol.

1050
00:59:09,831 --> 00:59:12,621
- She's been thinking about him all day.
- Right.

1051
00:59:12,621 --> 00:59:16,021
He was sick, too. She'll say, "Don't be sick."

1052
00:59:16,021 --> 00:59:18,631
- Wu Yeol is easy.
- Who's it?

1053
00:59:18,631 --> 00:59:20,531
I'm sure I'm right.

1054
00:59:20,531 --> 00:59:23,451
- Wu Yeol will text Gyu Ri.
- Gyu Ri?

1055
00:59:23,451 --> 00:59:27,481
He drove Yu Gyeong, and they had a great time.

1056
00:59:27,481 --> 00:59:30,031
But he's been aware of Gyu Ri all day.

1057
00:59:30,031 --> 00:59:35,401
He thinks he'll lose Gyu Ri forever
if he doesn't text her tonight.

1058
00:59:35,401 --> 00:59:37,601
- It's 100 percent Gyu Ri.
- 100 percent?

1059
00:59:37,601 --> 00:59:40,021
I think it will be Yu Gyeong.

1060
00:59:40,021 --> 00:59:41,861
- For today?
- It's Yu Gyeong.

1061
00:59:41,861 --> 00:59:44,961
I've been guessing Wu Yeol's moves correctly.

1062
00:59:44,961 --> 00:59:46,121
[That's hard to do]

1063
00:59:46,121 --> 00:59:47,701
You're like him.

1064
00:59:47,701 --> 00:59:50,721
He's saying, "I'm like him. It's Yu Gyeong."

1065
00:59:50,721 --> 00:59:53,081
- What do you say to that?
- I got nothing to say.

1066
00:59:53,081 --> 00:59:54,451
It is Yu Gyeong.

1067
00:59:54,451 --> 00:59:56,161
Let's go with Yu Gyeong.

1068
00:59:56,161 --> 01:00:00,681
And Seo Won seems more set now.

1069
01:00:00,681 --> 01:00:03,421
He cooked, hoping Gyu Ri would eat it.

1070
01:00:03,421 --> 01:00:06,141
Nothing major has happened,

1071
01:00:06,141 --> 01:00:08,551
but his feelings developed a lot.

1072
01:00:08,551 --> 01:00:14,711
It was like the quiet before the storm.

1073
01:00:14,711 --> 01:00:18,531
[It's time to send their fifth text tonight]

1074
01:00:21,341 --> 01:00:23,301
- What time do you go to bed?
- I went to bed at five.

1075
01:00:23,301 --> 01:00:25,401
- Why?
- I was writing the manuscript.

1076
01:00:25,401 --> 01:00:26,541
Really?

1077
01:00:26,541 --> 01:00:28,121
[She's been writing all night]

1078
01:00:28,121 --> 01:00:32,011
- Because you have work?
- Yes, the manuscript took some time.

1079
01:00:32,011 --> 01:00:33,771
But it's not tiring at all.

1080
01:00:33,771 --> 01:00:36,431
I'm not tired from going to bed at five, either.

1081
01:00:36,431 --> 01:00:38,441
She's cool.

1082
01:00:39,431 --> 01:00:42,231
[She can't muster the energy tonight]

1083
01:00:43,471 --> 01:00:45,531
- Min Ju.
- Yes.

1084
01:00:45,531 --> 01:00:47,121
Are you very sick?

1085
01:00:47,121 --> 01:00:49,401
Would you like water? Can I get you water?

1086
01:00:49,401 --> 01:00:52,331
- Warm water?
- I could really use it.

1087
01:00:57,581 --> 01:01:00,781
Yu Gyeong, what did you guys eat today?

1088
01:01:00,781 --> 01:01:04,571
Beef radish soup. I made an omelet.

1089
01:01:04,571 --> 01:01:06,461
- How was it?
- It turned out really well.

1090
01:01:06,461 --> 01:01:08,021
Really? Do you have any left?

1091
01:01:08,021 --> 01:01:12,161
Yes, we do. I made an omelet, too.

1092
01:01:12,161 --> 01:01:15,041
I made one this big.

1093
01:01:15,041 --> 01:01:17,951
Everyone ate so little tonight.

1094
01:01:17,951 --> 01:01:20,271
We have some left.

1095
01:01:20,271 --> 01:01:23,271
You have to try it. The soup is amazing.

1096
01:01:24,241 --> 01:01:26,301
Don't be sick.

1097
01:01:27,171 --> 01:01:29,121
[Smiling]

1098
01:01:30,411 --> 01:01:32,651
[Min Ju enters the kitchen]

1099
01:01:33,001 --> 01:01:34,981
Oh, hi.

1100
01:01:36,351 --> 01:01:38,921
- I'm not feeling well.
- Gosh, I'm sorry.

1101
01:01:38,921 --> 01:01:41,211
- Are you okay?
- No, I'm not.

1102
01:01:41,211 --> 01:01:43,641
Drink warm water. Would you like that stuff?

1103
01:01:43,641 --> 01:01:46,381
- What?
- Vitamins?

1104
01:01:46,381 --> 01:01:47,621
[Shaking head]

1105
01:01:47,621 --> 01:01:48,811
We have it.

1106
01:01:48,811 --> 01:01:50,841
But it's for men.

1107
01:01:51,861 --> 01:01:55,111
It probably wouldn't hurt.

1108
01:01:57,071 --> 01:01:58,181
Take it.

1109
01:01:58,181 --> 01:02:00,201
[Seong Min is giving her the vitamins]

1110
01:02:00,201 --> 01:02:01,541
It'd probably help.

1111
01:02:01,541 --> 01:02:04,891
- It'd help, although it's not medicine.
- But the smell...

1112
01:02:04,891 --> 01:02:07,181
- It's intense.
- You can't stomach it?

1113
01:02:07,181 --> 01:02:09,481
I'll take it tomorrow. Thank you.

1114
01:02:09,481 --> 01:02:11,721
It's too bad everyone's sick.

1115
01:02:12,851 --> 01:02:13,871
[Sigh]

1116
01:02:16,621 --> 01:02:18,841
Did you both catch a cold?

1117
01:02:23,191 --> 01:02:28,411
He didn't see me at dinner when he came home.

1118
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:32,211
He could've heard that I was sick.

1119
01:02:32,211 --> 01:02:34,511
[Groaning]

1120
01:02:34,511 --> 01:02:38,581
[When Yu Gyeong was sick,
he went out to get medicine]

1121
01:02:38,581 --> 01:02:41,441
He bought her the Beauty Digestive.

1122
01:02:41,441 --> 01:02:46,161
But he only asked me if I took medicine
when I was bedridden all day.

1123
01:02:46,161 --> 01:02:48,541
- It's unbelievable.
- I know.

1124
01:02:48,541 --> 01:02:54,491
[Comforting herself with the soup]

1125
01:02:54,491 --> 01:02:56,981
What? Are you eating alone?

1126
01:02:56,981 --> 01:03:00,111
Hold on. I'll sit with you after this.

1127
01:03:00,111 --> 01:03:02,051
Let's eat together.

1128
01:03:03,751 --> 01:03:06,911
- Her face looks leaner.
- I know.

1129
01:03:06,911 --> 01:03:08,301
[Wait for me]

1130
01:03:12,071 --> 01:03:14,611
[Eating while waiting]

1131
01:03:14,611 --> 01:03:17,751
Things aren't working out.

1132
01:03:17,751 --> 01:03:22,051
[Meanwhile, in the men's room]

1133
01:03:24,111 --> 01:03:26,771
Thank you for caring for me today.

1134
01:03:26,771 --> 01:03:29,151
- Min Ju.
- She switched. She's mad at Seong Min.

1135
01:03:29,151 --> 01:03:30,711
I know.

1136
01:03:31,561 --> 01:03:33,821
Not me.

1137
01:03:33,821 --> 01:03:35,461
I'm all about love.

1138
01:03:35,461 --> 01:03:37,611
Friendship over love? Or love over friendship?

1139
01:03:37,611 --> 01:03:39,591
[Dried Sweet Potato: See you tomorrow]

1140
01:03:39,591 --> 01:03:41,591
Seo Won got two texts.

1141
01:03:41,591 --> 01:03:45,311
[Gyu Ri also texted Seo Won]

1142
01:03:45,311 --> 01:03:48,551
He received as much as he gave today.

1143
01:03:49,841 --> 01:03:52,051
[Writing down the text result]

1144
01:03:52,051 --> 01:03:55,901
Sleepy Bear and Dried Sweet Potato.

1145
01:03:55,901 --> 01:03:57,481
I got two.

1146
01:03:58,301 --> 01:04:00,621
Crazy. Mr. Popular.

1147
01:04:00,621 --> 01:04:03,001
[His first time getting texts since he moved in]

1148
01:04:03,001 --> 01:04:05,721
I didn't know I was supposed to get a text.

1149
01:04:05,721 --> 01:04:07,821
He's so cute.

1150
01:04:08,671 --> 01:04:10,931
I felt amazing.

1151
01:04:10,931 --> 01:04:15,241
[He can't help but sing]

1152
01:04:17,201 --> 01:04:18,551
[Beluga of the Forest: You look good in white]

1153
01:04:18,551 --> 01:04:20,901
[Jun Hyeon sends a text to Gyu Ri]

1154
01:04:20,901 --> 01:04:22,891
[Tired Camel: Get some rest]

1155
01:04:22,891 --> 01:04:24,171
[Seo Won also texted Gyu Ri]

1156
01:04:24,171 --> 01:04:26,441
- Oh, my!
- They texted each other.

1157
01:04:36,791 --> 01:04:39,711
The most exciting moment today

1158
01:04:39,711 --> 01:04:43,561
was when I baked sweet potatoes with Seong Min.

1159
01:04:43,561 --> 01:04:47,151
When we baked sweet potatoes.

1160
01:04:47,151 --> 01:04:49,861
How do you do that with a sweet potato?

1161
01:04:49,861 --> 01:04:52,541
Something's up today. Today's the day.

1162
01:04:52,541 --> 01:04:54,521
You're definitely different.

1163
01:04:54,521 --> 01:04:56,921
My mood today?

1164
01:04:59,441 --> 01:05:03,641
I actually want to talk to Wu Yeol.

1165
01:05:03,641 --> 01:05:07,951
It feels like things are getting a little twisted.

1166
01:05:09,231 --> 01:05:11,221
I felt a little upset.

1167
01:05:11,221 --> 01:05:14,641
It could also be that her feelings
for him are growing.

1168
01:05:14,641 --> 01:05:21,391
I want to double-check if I'm right about it.

1169
01:05:21,391 --> 01:05:24,231
And I want to know how he feels.

1170
01:05:24,231 --> 01:05:27,171
I want to talk to him.

1171
01:05:29,091 --> 01:05:31,921
[After contemplating, Yu Gyeong texts Seong Min]

1172
01:05:31,921 --> 01:05:33,791
Seong Min?

1173
01:05:37,241 --> 01:05:40,451
[Busy Hamster: Everyone is getting sick.
Take care of yourself!]

1174
01:05:40,451 --> 01:05:41,941
One, two, three.

1175
01:05:41,941 --> 01:05:42,981
Ta-da!

1176
01:05:42,981 --> 01:05:45,271
What is it? How did you do it? But this is so...

1177
01:05:45,271 --> 01:05:48,711
[Someone who makes you happy]

1178
01:05:49,321 --> 01:05:52,101
[Yu Gyeong and Seong Min exchanged texts]

1179
01:05:53,291 --> 01:05:55,261
[Wu Yeol didn't get any text today]

1180
01:05:55,261 --> 01:05:57,091
This is bad.

1181
01:06:02,871 --> 01:06:05,351
Gosh, seriously...

1182
01:06:11,611 --> 01:06:14,831
- He's in bad mood.
- Oh, no.

1183
01:06:16,351 --> 01:06:24,441
[Where is Wu Yeol's heart?]

1184
01:06:24,441 --> 01:06:25,741
[Buzz]

1185
01:06:33,361 --> 01:06:37,001
[Salt Bread: I had fun thanks to you]

1186
01:06:37,001 --> 01:06:42,321
[Wu Yeol texted Yu Gyeong]

1187
01:06:42,321 --> 01:06:45,231
[Hanging around]

1188
01:06:47,121 --> 01:06:48,761
Oh, she wants to talk to him.

1189
01:06:48,761 --> 01:06:51,321
[Hanging around Wu Yeol's room to talk]

1190
01:06:52,171 --> 01:06:54,301
He's sick and sleeping.

1191
01:07:02,661 --> 01:07:09,011
[Continues to wait]

1192
01:07:22,741 --> 01:07:26,241
[Tossing and turning]

1193
01:07:35,271 --> 01:07:38,331
[Wu Yeol leaves the room]

1194
01:07:41,321 --> 01:07:45,861
Go to work tomorrow according to your schedule.

1195
01:07:46,921 --> 01:07:49,611
Sleep in more.

1196
01:07:49,611 --> 01:07:51,251
She wanted to tell him that?

1197
01:07:51,251 --> 01:07:55,591
[Tired]

1198
01:07:56,171 --> 01:07:59,381
- Did you get some sleep?
- Yeah, just now.

1199
01:08:00,481 --> 01:08:03,091
- What did you do?
- What did I do?

1200
01:08:03,091 --> 01:08:04,951
I waited for you.

1201
01:08:05,931 --> 01:08:08,331
To talk?

1202
01:08:11,551 --> 01:08:14,421
I'll see how I feel tomorrow and decide.

1203
01:08:17,081 --> 01:08:18,971
Well...

1204
01:08:18,971 --> 01:08:20,711
I don't know.

1205
01:08:22,461 --> 01:08:24,331
Oh, yeah...

1206
01:08:25,311 --> 01:08:28,921
- Sleep more.
- Look at her facial expression.

1207
01:08:33,251 --> 01:08:36,871
It must bother Yu Gyeong
that she didn't text him.

1208
01:08:37,871 --> 01:08:40,221
Are you still not feeling well? How bad is it?

1209
01:08:40,221 --> 01:08:43,541
My stomach hurts. My chest feels stuffy.

1210
01:08:43,541 --> 01:08:45,431
My tummy hurts.

1211
01:08:48,581 --> 01:08:50,611
And sweaty.

1212
01:08:57,291 --> 01:08:59,911
[Can't bring herself to talk]

1213
01:08:59,911 --> 01:09:01,691
Are you going to bed?

1214
01:09:06,121 --> 01:09:08,691
Yeah, I'll go to bed.

1215
01:09:13,321 --> 01:09:15,471
- Bye.
- Goodnight.

1216
01:09:26,201 --> 01:09:27,391
Gosh...

1217
01:09:28,721 --> 01:09:37,941
[Feeling frustrated even after talking]

1218
01:09:49,021 --> 01:09:51,701
- Are you okay?
- No.

1219
01:09:52,751 --> 01:09:54,781
Were you at work?

1220
01:09:55,851 --> 01:09:58,271
When did you get home?

1221
01:09:58,271 --> 01:10:04,871
[A part of her feels uneasy]

1222
01:10:04,871 --> 01:10:07,531
To us, it looks like romance.

1223
01:10:07,531 --> 01:10:12,661
I can only imagine how tormented they must feel.

1224
01:10:12,661 --> 01:10:15,881
As much as they have pushed away their feelings,

1225
01:10:15,881 --> 01:10:18,361
it will explode just as much.

1226
01:10:18,361 --> 01:10:19,691
[So worried]

1227
01:10:19,691 --> 01:10:21,051
I'm going crazy.

1228
01:10:21,051 --> 01:10:23,341
What if they had talked a little longer?

1229
01:10:23,341 --> 01:10:25,361
They would've hashed out more.

1230
01:10:25,361 --> 01:10:27,331
Working out what's bothering them.

1231
01:10:27,331 --> 01:10:30,341
For Wu Yeol, he's sick and feels out of it.

1232
01:10:30,341 --> 01:10:33,521
- He didn't get any texts.
- And on top of that,

1233
01:10:33,521 --> 01:10:38,461
he hasn't hashed out what
he should do going forward.

1234
01:10:38,461 --> 01:10:40,991
He might not have wanted to talk.

1235
01:10:40,991 --> 01:10:44,181
And he doesn't have energy for that.

1236
01:10:44,181 --> 01:10:48,001
[The city lights have descended]

1237
01:10:51,961 --> 01:10:53,681
The next evening.

1238
01:10:53,681 --> 01:10:55,521
[Sangsu-dong]

1239
01:10:58,391 --> 01:10:59,711
It's so funny.

1240
01:10:59,711 --> 01:11:02,541
[The ladies are headed somewhere]

1241
01:11:02,541 --> 01:11:04,911
Let's go up.

1242
01:11:07,511 --> 01:11:09,171
[At the house the night before]

1243
01:11:09,841 --> 01:11:11,991
We're going on a winter trip this week.

1244
01:11:11,991 --> 01:11:13,781
[Surprised]

1245
01:11:13,781 --> 01:11:15,131
- A trip?
- Already?

1246
01:11:15,131 --> 01:11:16,991
- It's Tuesday.
- A trip?

1247
01:11:16,991 --> 01:11:19,351
- Daebak.
- Where are we going?

1248
01:11:19,351 --> 01:11:21,781
- A trip?
- Love it.

1249
01:11:21,781 --> 01:11:23,791
What's this?

1250
01:11:23,791 --> 01:11:25,231
By tomorrow night at 8 p.m.

1251
01:11:25,231 --> 01:11:27,701
A winter trip? How fun!

1252
01:11:27,701 --> 01:11:30,751
Wow, no one is here.

1253
01:11:30,751 --> 01:11:32,961
How nice!

1254
01:11:32,961 --> 01:11:36,351
[The feast for the tenants]

1255
01:11:38,161 --> 01:11:41,411
Daebak. Chef Jung Ho Young?

1256
01:11:41,411 --> 01:11:44,271
[Dinner from Chef Jung Ho Young]

1257
01:11:44,271 --> 01:11:46,041
- Really?
- Really?

1258
01:11:46,041 --> 01:11:48,811
Really? I want to cry.

1259
01:11:48,811 --> 01:11:50,261
[Daebak]

1260
01:11:50,261 --> 01:11:53,021
I love this.

1261
01:11:53,021 --> 01:11:56,591
[Beautiful and clean Japanese cuisine]

1262
01:11:56,591 --> 01:11:58,021
Whoa...

1263
01:11:58,021 --> 01:12:00,721
Smells so good.

1264
01:12:00,721 --> 01:12:03,231
- Starting with the smell...
- I know.

1265
01:12:03,231 --> 01:12:05,361
What's all this?

1266
01:12:05,361 --> 01:12:06,781
I love it.

1267
01:12:06,781 --> 01:12:09,131
- The view is amazing, too.
- I know.

1268
01:12:09,131 --> 01:12:11,321
- Awesome view.
- What's all this?

1269
01:12:11,321 --> 01:12:14,741
- I had no idea a place like this existed.
- It's so nice.

1270
01:12:14,741 --> 01:12:16,841
[The dishes and view are both so perfect]

1271
01:12:18,911 --> 01:12:21,341
I love it.

1272
01:12:21,341 --> 01:12:23,481
- What is it?
- Are they going overseas?

1273
01:12:23,481 --> 01:12:25,681
[A brochure on Tokushima in every seat]

1274
01:12:26,621 --> 01:12:27,931
[Surprised]

1275
01:12:27,931 --> 01:12:30,821
Japan? Tokushima.

1276
01:12:31,681 --> 01:12:34,841
- It's Japan.
- Daebak.

1277
01:12:34,841 --> 01:12:37,201
I always wanted to go there.

1278
01:12:37,201 --> 01:12:39,511
- Look at this.
- It's so nice.

1279
01:12:39,511 --> 01:12:40,561
Daebak.

1280
01:12:40,561 --> 01:12:44,371
He's giving us a taste of Japan.

1281
01:12:44,371 --> 01:12:46,741
- In advance.
- Daebak.

1282
01:12:46,741 --> 01:12:48,421
Love it.

1283
01:12:48,421 --> 01:12:51,281
My heart is racing, thinking of going somewhere.

1284
01:12:51,281 --> 01:12:53,331
I love it.

1285
01:12:54,411 --> 01:12:56,131
[They're going to Japan together?]

1286
01:12:56,131 --> 01:12:58,651
The seating arrangements are important.

1287
01:12:58,651 --> 01:13:00,331
- Right.
- It's crucial.

1288
01:13:00,331 --> 01:13:03,611
The conversation on the plane feels different.

1289
01:13:03,611 --> 01:13:06,211
Traveling is so important.

1290
01:13:06,211 --> 01:13:08,061
There's someone who leads

1291
01:13:08,061 --> 01:13:10,301
and there are followers. They split like that.

1292
