[Isn't it so fun?]

1553
01:26:37,121 --> 01:26:39,921
Do you remember? The ladies...

1554
01:26:39,921 --> 01:26:44,701
When they first came to the house,
they were awkward and hesitant.

1555
01:26:44,701 --> 01:26:47,171
Right. They're usually like that.

1556
01:26:47,171 --> 01:26:50,151
But So Yun greeted them

1557
01:26:50,151 --> 01:26:53,011
and started leading the gathering.

1558
01:26:53,011 --> 01:26:55,821
When I saw her appearance at first,

1559
01:26:55,821 --> 01:26:59,071
- she was so pale and seemed so quiet.
- She seemed quiet.

1560
01:26:59,071 --> 01:27:01,451
- She seems demure.
- But when you see her...

1561
01:27:01,451 --> 01:27:04,271
she's aggressive and has a clear viewpoint.

1562
01:27:04,271 --> 01:27:09,861
She's a game-changer for sure.
I think she'll flip the script.

1563
01:27:09,861 --> 01:27:12,821
Thanks to So Yun, other ladies...

1564
01:27:12,821 --> 01:27:15,051
- They'll be motivated.
- They'll be motivated

1565
01:27:15,051 --> 01:27:18,461
- and speed things up or get honest.
- Right, right.

1566
01:27:18,461 --> 01:27:20,831
I think a situation can be created.

1567
01:27:20,831 --> 01:27:22,071
I think so.

1568
01:27:22,071 --> 01:27:24,081
Everyone is so cautious.

1569
01:27:24,081 --> 01:27:29,241
I think she can loosen up all
of that and boost things.

1570
01:27:29,241 --> 01:27:30,991
[It's time to get honest]

1571
01:27:30,991 --> 01:27:34,501
As soon as she got there, she suggested,
"Should we talk casually?"

1572
01:27:34,501 --> 01:27:39,151
All seven people were going at their
own pace for the last few days.

1573
01:27:39,151 --> 01:27:42,061
And a new person suggested speaking casually.

1574
01:27:42,061 --> 01:27:43,691
That's hard to do.

1575
01:27:43,691 --> 01:27:45,601
Wow, she did that right away.

1576
01:27:45,601 --> 01:27:48,461
And So Yun's suggestion shocked everyone.

1577
01:27:48,461 --> 01:27:51,411
She asked about everyone's ideal type.

1578
01:27:51,411 --> 01:27:54,781
It's the shortcut to gathering data.

1579
01:27:54,781 --> 01:27:56,881
It's a fast way to figure out everyone.

1580
01:27:56,881 --> 01:27:59,251
And it could be a way to flirt.

1581
01:27:59,251 --> 01:28:01,191
Makes you think, "That's me."

1582
01:28:01,191 --> 01:28:03,591
[Openly targeting]

1583
01:28:03,591 --> 01:28:07,741
A very cool-headed game-changer is here.

1584
01:28:07,741 --> 01:28:10,831
When I saw her first appear,

1585
01:28:10,831 --> 01:28:14,781
she kept looking toward the men as she spoke.

1586
01:28:14,781 --> 01:28:16,681
So, at first...

1587
01:28:16,681 --> 01:28:19,851
I thought, "Oh? What's this?"
But she had her reasons.

1588
01:28:19,851 --> 01:28:22,161
She said she decides within 3 seconds.

1589
01:28:22,161 --> 01:28:24,871
She scanned as soon as she got there

1590
01:28:24,871 --> 01:28:28,541
and thought, "It's him."
I think that's what she saw.

1591
01:28:28,541 --> 01:28:32,201
I think it all started from that moment.

1592
01:28:32,201 --> 01:28:34,471
- I give her that.
- Right.

1593
01:28:34,471 --> 01:28:37,401
She said she's dated someone she's pursued.

1594
01:28:37,401 --> 01:28:40,511
She proclaimed that there's someone she likes.

1595
01:28:40,511 --> 01:28:42,691
If she's interested in someone,

1596
01:28:42,691 --> 01:28:44,651
- she'll go for him.
- She bites it.

1597
01:28:44,651 --> 01:28:46,761
She's in attack mode.

1598
01:28:46,761 --> 01:28:48,821
She'll make her moves tomorrow.

1599
01:28:48,821 --> 01:28:51,231
I can somewhat predict it.

1600
01:28:51,231 --> 01:28:53,031
Are you all thinking the same?

1601
01:28:53,031 --> 01:28:54,461
I think I know who the 3-second man is.

1602
01:28:54,461 --> 01:28:56,481
- I think so, too.
- Wu Yeol?

1603
01:28:56,481 --> 01:28:58,751
She was staring at him so blatantly.

1604
01:28:58,751 --> 01:29:01,451
She scanned others but looked
at Wu Yeol a little longer.

1605
01:29:01,451 --> 01:29:03,531
- Wu Yeol again?
- Wu Yeol is used to this.

1606
01:29:03,531 --> 01:29:06,421
You're getting angry again.

1607
01:29:06,421 --> 01:29:09,441
Why do they only like Wu Yeol?
With so many men there.

1608
01:29:09,441 --> 01:29:10,601
[Here we go again]

1609
01:29:10,601 --> 01:29:13,331
A true game-changer has joined them.

1610
01:29:13,331 --> 01:29:17,251
She joined them a week later
and to catch up to them...

1611
01:29:17,251 --> 01:29:20,631
I think they'll be on even ground
within a day or two.

1612
01:29:20,631 --> 01:29:24,181
She caught up about two days'
worth in the last 30 minutes.

1613
01:29:24,181 --> 01:29:26,861
- Wow, daebak.
- Looking forward to this.

1614
01:29:26,861 --> 01:29:28,211
[Early morning before the sunrise]

1615
01:29:28,211 --> 01:29:29,831
It's morning.

1616
01:29:29,831 --> 01:29:33,751
[Jeong Gyu Ri wakes up, 5:15 a.m.]

1617
01:29:33,751 --> 01:29:37,301
[Seo Won and Gyu Ri are getting
ready earlier than usual]

1618
01:29:37,301 --> 01:29:38,941
I like Gyu Ri and Seo Won together.

1619
01:29:38,941 --> 01:29:43,101
How long does it take to get
to work if you take a car?

1620
01:29:43,101 --> 01:29:46,521
- About 20...
- Do you want to go to work together?

1621
01:29:46,521 --> 01:29:49,221
But I go to Dongdaemun tomorrow.

1622
01:29:49,221 --> 01:29:52,481
Really? Why didn't you say so?

1623
01:29:53,281 --> 01:29:55,141
What time do you leave tomorrow morning?

1624
01:29:55,141 --> 01:29:56,601
At 6:30.

1625
01:29:56,601 --> 01:29:58,261
Me, too.

1626
01:29:58,261 --> 01:30:01,231
My call time is at 7 a.m. at Dongdaemun.

1627
01:30:01,231 --> 01:30:03,621
- Dongdaemun?
- Fashion Week.

1628
01:30:03,621 --> 01:30:07,321
- The show...
- Oh, right. The show.

1629
01:30:08,901 --> 01:30:10,831
[Hesitant]

1630
01:30:11,471 --> 01:30:14,441
- Because everyone was there.
- Really?

1631
01:30:14,441 --> 01:30:16,731
Should we go together?

1632
01:30:16,731 --> 01:30:18,311
- Sounds good.
- She's accepting it.

1633
01:30:18,311 --> 01:30:20,411
So, you're going to DDP.

1634
01:30:20,411 --> 01:30:22,441
To check out the fabric.

1635
01:30:22,441 --> 01:30:24,241
Do you know where? To see the fabric?

1636
01:30:24,241 --> 01:30:27,491
- Where you see the fabric swatches?
- Of course.

1637
01:30:27,491 --> 01:30:29,801
What a coincidence, huh?

1638
01:30:29,801 --> 01:30:31,441
I know.

1639
01:30:33,041 --> 01:30:36,131
- Daebak.
- So neat. Really.

1640
01:30:36,131 --> 01:30:38,281
Go to Dongdaemun together.

1641
01:30:40,141 --> 01:30:43,761
[A little bit more exciting morning]

1642
01:30:43,761 --> 01:30:48,071
[Checking his clothes meticulously]

1643
01:30:49,631 --> 01:30:50,991
[Straight]

1644
01:30:52,911 --> 01:30:55,191
[Spraying cologne]

1645
01:30:57,451 --> 01:31:05,161
[Paying closer attention to the
reflection in the mirror]

1646
01:31:08,331 --> 01:31:11,881
Good morning.

1647
01:31:14,151 --> 01:31:17,041
I like Seo Won more the more I see him.

1648
01:31:17,041 --> 01:31:20,051
- Put the seatbelt on.
- Okay.

1649
01:31:20,051 --> 01:31:23,371
I'm glad I can give you a ride.

1650
01:31:23,371 --> 01:31:26,681
- How could this be?
- He's so chummy.

1651
01:31:26,681 --> 01:31:32,931
There aren't many times you get
to know a bunch of people at once.

1652
01:31:32,931 --> 01:31:37,231
There isn't. And no chance to live
together like this, either.

1653
01:31:37,231 --> 01:31:43,051
Since there are several of us here,
when I don't get

1654
01:31:43,051 --> 01:31:45,501
texts from someone who used to text me

1655
01:31:45,501 --> 01:31:48,511
and get new ones from someone new...

1656
01:31:48,511 --> 01:31:52,041
I just can't get used to it.

1657
01:31:53,241 --> 01:31:56,001
You must get many texts.

1658
01:31:56,001 --> 01:31:59,121
No, no, no.

1659
01:31:59,121 --> 01:32:02,281
- I'll drop you off here.
- What are you saying?

1660
01:32:02,281 --> 01:32:04,061
I'm so jealous.

1661
01:32:04,871 --> 01:32:07,601
Do you tend to cry a lot?

1662
01:32:07,601 --> 01:32:09,471
I learned that I do after I got here.

1663
01:32:09,471 --> 01:32:11,201
Come on. Already?

1664
01:32:11,201 --> 01:32:13,931
- I already cried once.
- Really? Really?

1665
01:32:13,931 --> 01:32:18,021
- But no one knows.
- No way.

1666
01:32:18,021 --> 01:32:24,151
I felt emotions I'd never felt before.

1667
01:32:24,151 --> 01:32:27,721
That's why I cried once.

1668
01:32:27,721 --> 01:32:31,921
- Are you sure you can tell me this?
- Yes. I want to tell you.

1669
01:32:33,241 --> 01:32:35,761
It must be someone other than me.

1670
01:32:35,761 --> 01:32:37,961
She must've thought of someone other than me.

1671
01:32:37,961 --> 01:32:40,301
- Right.
- He must've heard that.

1672
01:32:40,301 --> 01:32:42,621
I thought that was plausible.

1673
01:32:42,621 --> 01:32:45,801
It's easier for me if I think that.

1674
01:32:46,711 --> 01:32:48,331
It wasn't important who she cried for.

1675
01:32:48,331 --> 01:32:50,411
He's not dense.

1676
01:32:50,411 --> 01:32:52,541
But they didn't catch me.

1677
01:32:52,541 --> 01:32:54,931
Good, good.

1678
01:32:54,931 --> 01:32:57,311
You should cry if you're sad.

1679
01:32:58,641 --> 01:33:02,581
- Laugh if you're happy.
- Seo Won can put you at ease.

1680
01:33:02,581 --> 01:33:05,041
He's the real deal.

1681
01:33:06,161 --> 01:33:10,021
- We're here, right?
- We're at DDP.

1682
01:33:10,021 --> 01:33:13,721
[Looking through]

1683
01:33:13,721 --> 01:33:16,501
It's not much. A vitamin candy.

1684
01:33:16,501 --> 01:33:17,971
- Whoa.
- So smart!

1685
01:33:17,971 --> 01:33:20,101
- It's a gift.
- He's the best.

1686
01:33:20,101 --> 01:33:23,881
- Be careful. Don't forget your things.
- Okay.

1687
01:33:25,771 --> 01:33:29,861
- Fighting! Good luck!
- Fighting! Bye!

1688
01:33:33,931 --> 01:33:35,271
[Staring]

1689
01:33:35,271 --> 01:33:37,411
It'll be a good day.

1690
01:33:38,171 --> 01:33:39,941
He gave it to her so nonchalantly.

1691
01:33:39,941 --> 01:33:43,991
[Early morning commute, what's he feeling?]

1692
01:33:43,991 --> 01:33:46,391
Seo Won is pretty nice.

1693
01:33:46,391 --> 01:33:48,841
- This was great.
- Really.

1694
01:33:48,841 --> 01:33:50,421
Seo Won is my one pick.

1695
01:33:50,421 --> 01:33:53,351
He's a softie but tough on the outside.

1696
01:33:53,351 --> 01:33:57,991
He always considers the other person first.

1697
01:33:57,991 --> 01:34:01,471
He seems inattentive, yet he looks out for you

1698
01:34:01,471 --> 01:34:03,291
and has you figured out.

1699
01:34:03,291 --> 01:34:08,151
And Seo Won realized that
Gyu Ri liked someone else.

1700
01:34:08,151 --> 01:34:10,691
He realized it.

1701
01:34:10,691 --> 01:34:13,891
But I liked how he behaved after that talk.

1702
01:34:13,891 --> 01:34:15,401
"That's plausible."

1703
01:34:15,401 --> 01:34:17,001
He's cool.

1704
01:34:17,001 --> 01:34:21,081
I hope Gyu Ri can really see Seo Won.

1705
01:34:24,251 --> 01:34:28,331
[Bright morning]

1706
01:34:28,331 --> 01:34:33,881
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong are busy getting ready]

1707
01:34:39,111 --> 01:34:41,801
Hi.

1708
01:34:41,801 --> 01:34:45,451
Wu Yeol is a bit miffed for not getting a text.

1709
01:34:49,641 --> 01:34:52,771
[Moving toward her]

1710
01:34:54,101 --> 01:34:57,281
[No reaction from Yu Gyeong]

1711
01:35:03,271 --> 01:35:06,221
- What are you taking?
- Subway.

1712
01:35:06,221 --> 01:35:08,701
- Want a ride to the station?
- Nope.

1713
01:35:09,711 --> 01:35:13,311
- She turned him down.
- She's drawing the line.

1714
01:35:14,511 --> 01:35:15,851
[Wave]

1715
01:35:18,341 --> 01:35:20,171
Oh, my God!

1716
01:35:21,001 --> 01:35:24,561
- She's really drawing the line.
- How did this happen overnight?

1717
01:35:24,561 --> 01:35:25,961
She's determined.

1718
01:35:25,961 --> 01:35:30,591
[A little change in temperature]

1719
01:35:30,591 --> 01:35:32,211
Wow, really?

1720
01:35:32,211 --> 01:35:34,581
Is Yu Gyeong starting to detach?

1721
01:35:34,581 --> 01:35:36,181
- She's trying.
- Determined?

1722
01:35:36,181 --> 01:35:38,141
- Trying.
- That was a first.

1723
01:35:38,141 --> 01:35:40,451
And when she walked away,

1724
01:35:40,451 --> 01:35:43,281
she didn't turn around. She walked away fast.

1725
01:35:43,281 --> 01:35:46,501
That looked more like she was trying hard.

1726
01:35:46,501 --> 01:35:50,281
But for Wu Yeol, it's a bit preposterous.

1727
01:35:50,281 --> 01:35:54,781
- True.
- They had a good time carpooling.

1728
01:35:54,781 --> 01:35:58,631
And came back after work,
but Yu Gyeong is so cold.

1729
01:35:58,631 --> 01:36:02,891
Wu Yeol would think she was
so happy in the morning,

1730
01:36:02,891 --> 01:36:05,771
talking about going to the movies

1731
01:36:05,771 --> 01:36:10,851
and she's all lovey-dovey with
Seong Min while he was sick.

1732
01:36:10,851 --> 01:36:14,721
So, Wu Yeol can be more resentful of Yu Gyeong.

1733
01:36:14,721 --> 01:36:18,891
Roy, I can't believe you're speaking for Wu Yeol.

1734
01:36:18,891 --> 01:36:22,441
Wu Yeol, I looked out for you for once.

1735
01:36:23,351 --> 01:36:29,061
[Evening already]

1736
01:36:31,491 --> 01:36:36,741
[So Yun is waiting for someone in anticipation]

1737
01:36:36,741 --> 01:36:40,351
I think I decide in the first 3 seconds.

1738
01:36:40,351 --> 01:36:41,831
Did you decide?

1739
01:36:41,831 --> 01:36:43,391
Yes, I did.

1740
01:36:43,391 --> 01:36:45,961
[Ms. Choi So Yun, you can go on a date
with someone you're interested in]

1741
01:36:45,961 --> 01:36:47,681
I wonder how she feels.

1742
01:36:47,681 --> 01:36:49,341
[She chooses after much contemplation]

1743
01:36:51,751 --> 01:36:53,351
Wu Yeol.

1744
01:36:53,351 --> 01:36:56,121
[Who did So Yun choose?]

1745
01:37:00,791 --> 01:37:02,661
- Who?
- Really?

1746
01:37:04,481 --> 01:37:06,241
My gosh.

1747
01:37:10,281 --> 01:37:11,841
[Surprised]

1748
01:37:11,841 --> 01:37:13,221
Hello.

1749
01:37:13,221 --> 01:37:16,081
- Did you wait long?
- No worries.

1750
01:37:17,211 --> 01:37:19,591
- Did you come right after work?
- Yes.

1751
01:37:21,081 --> 01:37:25,451
- I thought you might be waiting in the cold.
- Let's see.

1752
01:37:25,451 --> 01:37:29,151
You look so tall today.

1753
01:37:30,541 --> 01:37:36,581
Actually, I'm wearing the tallest heels I have.

1754
01:37:36,581 --> 01:37:38,571
Really?

1755
01:37:40,001 --> 01:37:42,301
- I felt...
- Go ahead.

1756
01:37:42,301 --> 01:37:44,531
I wanted our height to match.

1757
01:37:44,531 --> 01:37:46,441
I'm fine either way.

1758
01:37:46,441 --> 01:37:48,201
[Hehe]

1759
01:37:48,201 --> 01:37:51,521
- Did you eat lunch?
- I did.

1760
01:37:51,521 --> 01:37:52,821
What did you eat?

1761
01:37:52,821 --> 01:37:55,551
Rice bowl.

1762
01:37:55,551 --> 01:37:57,231
How filling.

1763
01:37:57,231 --> 01:37:59,171
Move inside.

1764
01:38:01,931 --> 01:38:05,941
[A restaurant in Seongdong-gu]

1765
01:38:15,721 --> 01:38:17,681
[Stealing a look]

1766
01:38:27,641 --> 01:38:29,971
[Tense]

1767
01:38:30,491 --> 01:38:34,361
You said you eat everything but seafood, right?

1768
01:38:34,361 --> 01:38:37,451
- But you eat shrimp tempura?
- Yes.

1769
01:38:37,451 --> 01:38:40,011
You have a good memory.

1770
01:38:40,011 --> 01:38:42,591
Wu Yeol remembers everything.

1771
01:38:42,591 --> 01:38:43,971
[Holding]

1772
01:38:43,971 --> 01:38:46,691
- And she's a year older than him.
- Perfect.

1773
01:38:46,691 --> 01:38:48,481
- Menu...
- Should I look at that?

1774
01:38:48,481 --> 01:38:50,581
Should we look together?

1775
01:38:57,161 --> 01:38:59,561
What would you like to eat?

1776
01:38:59,561 --> 01:39:02,761
- Let me hold it.
- Nice.

1777
01:39:02,761 --> 01:39:06,511
[Fidgeting]

1778
01:39:06,871 --> 01:39:08,431
Do you like pasta?

1779
01:39:08,431 --> 01:39:10,761
What did you say you had for lunch?

1780
01:39:12,341 --> 01:39:15,181
Pasta and kimchi fried rice.

1781
01:39:15,181 --> 01:39:17,021
Let's eat something else.

1782
01:39:17,021 --> 01:39:20,891
Boneless short ribs are their
signature dish. Should we get that?

1783
01:39:20,891 --> 01:39:23,091
Boneless short ribs? Sounds good.

1784
01:39:23,091 --> 01:39:26,181
One boneless short ribs and gnocchi?

1785
01:39:26,181 --> 01:39:27,821
Sounds good.

1786
01:39:32,891 --> 01:39:34,841
[Looking]

1787
01:39:37,151 --> 01:39:39,241
How is it going? You came yesterday.

1788
01:39:40,101 --> 01:39:42,491
- I feel so out of it.
- Right?

1789
01:39:44,011 --> 01:39:46,791
Did you expect anything from the house?

1790
01:39:47,791 --> 01:39:52,901
I wanted to cook with everyone.

1791
01:39:52,901 --> 01:39:55,811
Are you a good cook? You said you live alone.

1792
01:39:55,811 --> 01:40:00,511
It's not easy to eat properly when you live alone.

1793
01:40:00,511 --> 01:40:03,581
- I just eat the usual stuff.
- Right.

1794
01:40:04,811 --> 01:40:06,931
It's hard to clean up, right?

1795
01:40:07,811 --> 01:40:09,431
I like cleaning up.

1796
01:40:09,431 --> 01:40:10,651
Really?

1797
01:40:10,651 --> 01:40:12,771
I like cleaning.

1798
01:40:12,771 --> 01:40:17,881
- Even doing dishes?
- I do the dishes right away.

1799
01:40:17,881 --> 01:40:21,651
I've never met anyone who likes cleaning.

1800
01:40:21,651 --> 01:40:24,311
Being clean is very attractive.

1801
01:40:24,311 --> 01:40:26,741
Do you need to clean?

1802
01:40:30,021 --> 01:40:31,121
Can I call you if I need help?

1803
01:40:31,121 --> 01:40:33,081
- Sure. Call me.
- Sounds good.

1804
01:40:33,081 --> 01:40:35,951
You have to joke back as she does.

1805
01:40:35,951 --> 01:40:37,881
[Truffle gnocchi is served]

1806
01:40:37,881 --> 01:40:40,151
Thank you.

1807
01:40:42,601 --> 01:40:45,481
- Do you want some?
- See? She doesn't back down.

1808
01:40:45,481 --> 01:40:47,181
Thank you.

1809
01:40:49,091 --> 01:40:52,461
Do you like truffles?

1810
01:40:52,461 --> 01:40:55,961
I do. Can't eat it because it's not around.

1811
01:40:55,961 --> 01:41:00,191
I'm not sure if I should be
served first, but thank you.

1812
01:41:02,841 --> 01:41:04,701
I haven't had gnocchi too much.

1813
01:41:04,701 --> 01:41:07,121
Really?

1814
01:41:07,121 --> 01:41:10,371
I haven't had a lot of dishes.

1815
01:41:11,341 --> 01:41:13,291
[Cute]

1816
01:41:13,291 --> 01:41:17,161
I get to try a lot of different foods here.

1817
01:41:17,161 --> 01:41:20,141
What did you like the most since you got here?

1818
01:41:26,561 --> 01:41:28,551
I'll tell you after I try this.

1819
01:41:28,551 --> 01:41:31,141
Look how smooth he is.

1820
01:41:36,331 --> 01:41:38,311
[Tasting]

1821
01:41:40,061 --> 01:41:41,841
[Anticipating]

1822
01:41:44,201 --> 01:41:46,031
Gnocchi.

1823
01:41:46,031 --> 01:41:48,641
- They're getting closer.
- They're cute.

1824
01:41:49,871 --> 01:41:51,871
You're quick.

1825
01:41:56,211 --> 01:41:59,411
Will you change your mind
after trying the short ribs?

1826
01:42:01,641 --> 01:42:05,581
It still means I'm enjoying today's food the most.

1827
01:42:06,511 --> 01:42:09,181
- Isn't that nice?
- Sure.

1828
01:42:14,711 --> 01:42:17,941
- I have a question.
- What is it?

1829
01:42:17,941 --> 01:42:20,411
How was my first impression?

1830
01:42:20,411 --> 01:42:23,021
- Your first impression?
- Yes.

1831
01:42:23,021 --> 01:42:28,721
[Thinking back to their first meeting]

1832
01:42:30,541 --> 01:42:33,821
- First impression...
- I'm so curious.

1833
01:42:33,821 --> 01:42:36,521
[Anticipation]

1834
01:42:36,521 --> 01:42:38,161
Kind of...

1835
01:42:42,821 --> 01:42:45,081
- like a cat?
- A cat?

1836
01:42:45,081 --> 01:42:46,991
Really?

1837
01:42:46,991 --> 01:42:49,151
- I've never heard that before.
- Really?

1838
01:42:49,151 --> 01:42:51,841
- I felt like you were a cat.
- Really?

1839
01:42:51,841 --> 01:42:55,091
- He's interested. He said he liked cats.
- That's right!

1840
01:42:55,091 --> 01:42:56,291
[Grin]

1841
01:42:57,761 --> 01:43:00,641
Do you like dogs or cats?

1842
01:43:00,641 --> 01:43:02,391
My gosh...

1843
01:43:04,281 --> 01:43:06,391
I'm a dog...

1844
01:43:07,171 --> 01:43:09,841
- I'm not a cat.
- Right.

1845
01:43:13,181 --> 01:43:15,281
A cat?

1846
01:43:17,431 --> 01:43:19,931
Was I fishing too much?

1847
01:43:19,931 --> 01:43:21,581
No.

1848
01:43:23,461 --> 01:43:26,601
- You said you liked dogs.
- Correct.

1849
01:43:27,801 --> 01:43:30,381
I remember everything.

1850
01:43:30,381 --> 01:43:34,751
- Isn't that creepy?
- No. I like it.

1851
01:43:36,641 --> 01:43:40,241
You said your parents live in Yangpyeong, right?

1852
01:43:40,241 --> 01:43:42,931
- I remember everything, too.
- They're both...

1853
01:43:42,931 --> 01:43:46,571
- Daechi-dong, right?
- Yes.

1854
01:43:51,641 --> 01:43:54,531
She's different from Gyu Ri or Yu Gyeong.

1855
01:43:54,531 --> 01:43:56,701
Totally different.

1856
01:43:56,701 --> 01:43:59,701
So Yun doesn't cry. She just goes head-on.

1857
01:43:59,701 --> 01:44:01,751
Head-on?

1858
01:44:02,631 --> 01:44:07,161
But it's not too much. It's just unique.

1859
01:44:07,161 --> 01:44:11,151
[The conversation deepens over wine]

1860
01:44:14,381 --> 01:44:17,871
- Have you done a lot of dating?
- Dating?

1861
01:44:17,871 --> 01:44:21,971
No, I'm not that experienced.

1862
01:44:21,971 --> 01:44:25,921
- How many times?
- Long-term relationships.

1863
01:44:25,921 --> 01:44:28,321
You tend to be with someone for a long time?

1864
01:44:28,321 --> 01:44:31,471
She is so likable.

1865
01:44:34,051 --> 01:44:36,911
[Grins]

1866
01:44:36,911 --> 01:44:38,781
I'll bring out the boneless short ribs.

1867
01:44:38,781 --> 01:44:41,331
Thank you.

1868
01:44:41,331 --> 01:44:44,341
- Let me slice it.
- Thank you.

1869
01:44:45,741 --> 01:44:48,771
- Do you like big bites?
- No, I prefer small.

1870
01:44:48,771 --> 01:44:50,561
Very small?

1871
01:44:50,561 --> 01:44:53,731
Look at So Yun's shoulders scrunch up.

1872
01:44:53,731 --> 01:44:57,111
[Chop chop]

1873
01:44:57,111 --> 01:44:59,361
- How's the width?
- Good.

1874
01:44:59,361 --> 01:45:02,181
- Too big?
- No, it's okay.

1875
01:45:02,181 --> 01:45:05,371
If it's too big, I can cut it more.

1876
01:45:05,371 --> 01:45:07,371
[Hehe]

1877
01:45:12,011 --> 01:45:14,871
- Thank you.
- No problem.

1878
01:45:19,551 --> 01:45:21,311
[Yum]

1879
01:45:23,021 --> 01:45:25,421
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1880
01:45:34,721 --> 01:45:36,271
Is it good?

1881
01:45:39,681 --> 01:45:42,301
I'm changing my favorite food to short ribs.

1882
01:45:42,301 --> 01:45:44,261
[Hilarious]

1883
01:45:44,261 --> 01:45:47,901
He's good at setting the pace.

1884
01:45:49,161 --> 01:45:51,451
I want to know something else.

1885
01:45:51,451 --> 01:45:53,261
Ask me.

1886
01:45:53,261 --> 01:45:59,841
How would your friends describe your personality?

1887
01:45:59,841 --> 01:46:03,461
If I get close to someone, I can act cute.

1888
01:46:05,691 --> 01:46:07,871
I can be playful.

1889
01:46:09,261 --> 01:46:12,411
Do you act cute to your friends?

1890
01:46:13,821 --> 01:46:15,771
I think so.

1891
01:46:15,771 --> 01:46:18,401
Maybe I shouldn't call it cute.

1892
01:46:18,401 --> 01:46:21,871
Pouting?

1893
01:46:21,871 --> 01:46:24,031
Something like that.

1894
01:46:25,271 --> 01:46:27,581
Can I look forward to it?

1895
01:46:28,991 --> 01:46:31,261
Look forward to it?

1896
01:46:31,261 --> 01:46:33,691
Sure, look forward to it.

1897
01:46:35,741 --> 01:46:39,841
Are you going to practice tonight?

1898
01:46:40,701 --> 01:46:43,021
I don't need practice.

1899
01:46:43,021 --> 01:46:45,701
- You're confident?
- I'm confident.

1900
01:46:49,101 --> 01:46:51,711
What is your personality like?

1901
01:46:51,711 --> 01:46:53,131
Me?

1902
01:46:53,981 --> 01:46:58,471
You might not believe me,
but I'm the comic with my friends.

1903
01:47:00,771 --> 01:47:03,511
I believe you.

1904
01:47:04,551 --> 01:47:07,521
- I can see it.
- Really?

1905
01:47:10,151 --> 01:47:12,931
Are you good at adjusting?

1906
01:47:12,931 --> 01:47:16,051
To new environments and such.

1907
01:47:16,051 --> 01:47:17,911
Yes. I think I'm good at that.

1908
01:47:17,911 --> 01:47:21,791
It feels like you might move a little faster

1909
01:47:22,881 --> 01:47:26,461
than the people who were here before.

1910
01:47:26,461 --> 01:47:29,031
- I'm not worried.
- He gets it.

1911
01:47:29,031 --> 01:47:34,521
Really? You're not worried about my fast pace?

1912
01:47:35,981 --> 01:47:37,961
I can keep up.

1913
01:47:37,961 --> 01:47:40,381
I can keep up with anything.

1914
01:47:46,221 --> 01:47:53,561
So, isn't it awkward to use honorifics?

1915
01:47:53,561 --> 01:47:54,941
Crazy.

1916
01:47:54,941 --> 01:48:01,141
I was going to bring that up today.

1917
01:48:06,891 --> 01:48:08,391
Should we?

1918
01:48:08,391 --> 01:48:10,491
Let's do it.

1919
01:48:10,491 --> 01:48:13,211
What should I call you, then?

1920
01:48:14,301 --> 01:48:17,831
You might not like being called "noona."

1921
01:48:17,831 --> 01:48:19,641
- He's cute.
- Right?

1922
01:48:19,641 --> 01:48:22,701
Let's start with "noona" for now.

1923
01:48:23,681 --> 01:48:27,091
- Okay, Noona.
- My goodness!

1924
01:48:27,091 --> 01:48:29,951
- It's comfortable.
- I've never...

1925
01:48:29,951 --> 01:48:31,271
Is this your first time?

1926
01:48:31,271 --> 01:48:33,351
You're the first guy here.

1927
01:48:33,351 --> 01:48:37,611
- I see.
- This is exciting.

1928
01:48:37,611 --> 01:48:40,791
I tend to switch to speaking casually soon.

1929
01:48:41,751 --> 01:48:45,121
But things haven't been going as expected.

1930
01:48:50,481 --> 01:48:53,351
Do you tend to feel certain early?

1931
01:48:53,351 --> 01:48:55,161
She's speaking down to him.

1932
01:48:56,521 --> 01:49:02,371
- Good question.
- Maybe about after three dates?

1933
01:49:02,371 --> 01:49:03,791
Three dates.

1934
01:49:03,791 --> 01:49:06,481
I get a vibe after three dates.

1935
01:49:06,481 --> 01:49:13,401
Depending on how they are,
I might change my stance.

1936
01:49:14,991 --> 01:49:18,411
So, you're accommodating.

1937
01:49:18,411 --> 01:49:21,211
That feels good to me.

1938
01:49:21,211 --> 01:49:24,351
Do you tend to accommodate
in a relationship, too?

1939
01:49:25,231 --> 01:49:27,081
I think so.

1940
01:49:30,461 --> 01:49:32,041
How commendable.

1941
01:49:32,961 --> 01:49:36,591
Commendable? Is that good?

1942
01:49:36,591 --> 01:49:37,661
It is.

1943
01:49:37,661 --> 01:49:40,131
- He's met his match.
- He's in trouble.

1944
01:49:48,731 --> 01:49:52,871
What do you like, older, younger,
or the same age?

1945
01:49:52,871 --> 01:49:55,641
I've always gone for older women.

1946
01:49:55,641 --> 01:49:57,041
Why?

1947
01:49:58,491 --> 01:50:02,651
I feel like I can banter more with someone older.

1948
01:50:02,651 --> 01:50:05,151
This is legendary banter.

1949
01:50:05,151 --> 01:50:08,631
It might be because I'm less experienced, though.

1950
01:50:11,001 --> 01:50:14,031
- Have you dated a younger guy?
- This is important.

1951
01:50:14,031 --> 01:50:15,601
Yes.

1952
01:50:16,881 --> 01:50:21,671
You seem like someone
who leads in a relationship.

1953
01:50:21,671 --> 01:50:23,371
Me?

1954
01:50:28,491 --> 01:50:30,521
I think it depends on the person.

1955
01:50:30,521 --> 01:50:32,661
You said you just need 3 seconds.

1956
01:50:32,661 --> 01:50:35,681
I don't like ambiguity.

1957
01:50:35,681 --> 01:50:37,381
It has to be this or that.

1958
01:50:37,381 --> 01:50:38,791
It seems like it.

1959
01:50:38,791 --> 01:50:42,381
- She's clear.
- So attractive.

1960
01:50:42,381 --> 01:50:45,521
I think I've fallen for So Yun.

1961
01:50:45,521 --> 01:50:46,801
[Falling in love]

1962
01:50:47,621 --> 01:50:52,921
So, do you usually make the first move?

1963
01:50:52,921 --> 01:50:56,721
Or the other person?

1964
01:50:56,721 --> 01:50:59,801
- I usually do.
- You do.

1965
01:51:01,801 --> 01:51:04,081
We're similar in that, too.

1966
01:51:06,291 --> 01:51:08,461
Do you have an idea now?

1967
01:51:08,461 --> 01:51:10,181
- Of you?
- Yes.

1968
01:51:16,011 --> 01:51:18,831
No, I need to get to know you more.

1969
01:51:18,831 --> 01:51:21,771
"I need to get to know you more." So cute.

1970
01:51:22,801 --> 01:51:25,521
Do you feel like you have an idea of me?

1971
01:51:27,071 --> 01:51:31,571
I need to see you at least three times.

1972
01:51:31,571 --> 01:51:34,351
It's a bit too early now.

1973
01:51:36,081 --> 01:51:38,551
- Are you done?
- Yes.

1974
01:51:44,821 --> 01:51:46,391
It's good.

1975
01:51:48,971 --> 01:51:51,441
[Glancing]

1976
01:51:55,671 --> 01:51:57,781
Could you ring us up?

1977
01:51:57,781 --> 01:51:59,311
[Taking out wallet]

1978
01:51:59,311 --> 01:52:02,061
- I got it.
- Thanks.

1979
01:52:02,061 --> 01:52:05,701
- I'll get you something tastier next time.
- Okay.

1980
01:52:08,321 --> 01:52:10,551
[A new meeting, exciting beginning]

1981
01:52:10,551 --> 01:52:13,701
[Are their hearts as close as their conversation?]

1982
01:52:13,701 --> 01:52:15,581
That was so good.

1983
01:52:15,581 --> 01:52:17,771
Insane.

1984
01:52:17,771 --> 01:52:19,551
We haven't had energy like this.

1985
01:52:19,551 --> 01:52:21,281
It's a different energy.

1986
01:52:21,281 --> 01:52:23,821
It's a different level.

1987
01:52:23,821 --> 01:52:27,001
Wow, I was watching the two of them...

1988
01:52:27,001 --> 01:52:31,011
There was a tightrope between them.

1989
01:52:31,011 --> 01:52:32,971
Doesn't this make things complicated?

1990
01:52:32,971 --> 01:52:34,761
So one person got added.

1991
01:52:34,761 --> 01:52:36,621
Wu Yeol must be going crazy.

1992
01:52:36,621 --> 01:52:41,521
For him to enjoy today,
he was holding himself back.

1993
01:52:41,521 --> 01:52:45,521
- We should see how he's feeling.
- He needs to act wisely now.

1994
01:52:45,521 --> 01:52:47,511
- At the house...
- This is trouble.

1995
01:52:47,511 --> 01:52:50,801
they'll be talking casually while others aren't.

1996
01:52:50,801 --> 01:52:53,271
I can already see Yu Gyeong hurting.

1997
01:52:53,271 --> 01:52:56,151
- What about Gyu Ri?
- Everyone is going to be there...

1998
01:52:56,151 --> 01:53:00,241
Compared to the two, So Yun is bold.

1999
01:53:00,241 --> 01:53:01,831
She'll sit next to him first.

2000
01:53:01,831 --> 01:53:04,741
Yu Gyeong can't get between them.

2001
01:53:04,741 --> 01:53:06,421
She'll put her arms around him.

2002
01:53:06,421 --> 01:53:09,681
If he walks up to Gyu Ri, So Yun will trip him.

2003
01:53:09,681 --> 01:53:14,231
Or tell him to sit next to her, or on her lap.

2004
01:53:14,231 --> 01:53:17,711
I hear a storm came to the
Signal House that night.

2005
01:53:17,711 --> 01:53:20,331
- Let's see it!
- Now!

2006
01:53:26,671 --> 01:53:30,771
[Yu Gyeong gets home late]

2007
01:53:32,591 --> 01:53:34,761
[Looking around]

2008
01:53:40,801 --> 01:53:42,691
- Unni?
- What's going on?

2009
01:53:42,691 --> 01:53:45,191
When did you get home?

2010
01:53:45,191 --> 01:53:49,621
Me? About two hours ago.

2011
01:53:49,621 --> 01:53:51,171
Is no one else home?

2012
01:53:51,171 --> 01:53:56,361
I think Seo Won is here, but he's sleeping.

2013
01:53:56,361 --> 01:53:59,011
He had a show at 6:30.

2014
01:53:59,971 --> 01:54:02,171
I know nothing.

2015
01:54:03,751 --> 01:54:07,531
I had dance and class at school today.

2016
01:54:09,161 --> 01:54:12,321
[Yu Gyeong suddenly starts to cry]

2017
01:54:12,321 --> 01:54:15,341
- Are you having a hard time?
- She's crying.

2018
01:54:15,341 --> 01:54:17,961
I think I need to cry more.

2019
01:54:17,961 --> 01:54:21,681
My gosh. What's happening? What's going on?

2020
01:54:21,681 --> 01:54:23,871
[Door closes]

2021
01:54:23,871 --> 01:54:26,841
She doesn't feel good about
what happened in the morning.

2022
01:54:26,841 --> 01:54:29,331
She likes Wu Yeol for real.

2023
01:54:31,631 --> 01:54:34,211
Yu Gyeong, what's wrong?

2024
01:54:35,111 --> 01:54:37,211
Yu Gyeong, what's wrong?

2025
01:54:39,471 --> 01:54:42,961
She still likes him so much.

2026
01:54:42,961 --> 01:54:45,301
Don't cry. What's wrong?

2027
01:54:49,771 --> 01:54:53,141
- This is crazy.
- Really?

2028
01:54:53,141 --> 01:54:56,171
What's going on?

2029
01:54:57,561 --> 01:55:00,611
It's okay. You can cry.

2030
01:55:02,531 --> 01:55:05,631
Thank goodness Min Ju is here.

2031
01:55:05,631 --> 01:55:08,101
Aigoo, her eyes are all red.

2032
01:55:08,101 --> 01:55:11,631
I thought I was okay yesterday.

2033
01:55:12,591 --> 01:55:14,821
I was.

2034
01:55:14,821 --> 01:55:21,031
But I did know inside that I was avoiding this.

2035
01:55:21,031 --> 01:55:23,041
That's right.

2036
01:55:25,741 --> 01:55:27,311
Are you going to bed?

2037
01:55:28,271 --> 01:55:30,481
[Leans back]

2038
01:55:30,481 --> 01:55:34,871
We're not in alignment.

2039
01:55:37,751 --> 01:55:40,231
Yeah, I'll go to bed.

2040
01:55:42,891 --> 01:55:48,951
[Tried to coldly turn her back,
but disappointment remained]

2041
01:55:52,451 --> 01:55:55,221
I thought it was over.

2042
01:55:56,411 --> 01:56:01,101
I thought I should just get over it.

2043
01:56:01,101 --> 01:56:07,601
[A strange air between them]

2044
01:56:09,811 --> 01:56:14,051
It's better for me this way,

2045
01:56:14,051 --> 01:56:18,291
so I won't suffer too much.

2046
01:56:19,471 --> 01:56:23,931
I fell for him so quickly.

2047
01:56:26,331 --> 01:56:28,401
I shouldn't have.

2048
01:56:32,121 --> 01:56:41,581
I tried hard not to feel anything about him.

2049
01:56:41,581 --> 01:56:43,131
But in my heart...

2050
01:56:43,131 --> 01:56:46,211
- Of course.
- It doesn't work.

2051
01:56:46,211 --> 01:56:48,111
I see.

2052
01:56:50,681 --> 01:56:55,511
I wanted to push it down more.

2053
01:56:55,511 --> 01:56:58,601
Because it's better this way.

2054
01:56:58,601 --> 01:57:03,401
If you push it down, it comes back even harder.

2055
01:57:05,381 --> 01:57:09,431
- I hate him.
- Me, too.

2056
01:57:09,431 --> 01:57:12,151
You had it harder than I thought.

2057
01:57:15,351 --> 01:57:19,171
I think things could always change.

2058
01:57:19,171 --> 01:57:24,761
It could be different on our trip tomorrow.

2059
01:57:24,761 --> 01:57:26,941
They have to go on a trip now. Oh, no...

2060
01:57:26,941 --> 01:57:30,281
I think he wants to get to know many people.

2061
01:57:30,281 --> 01:57:37,051
He's doing that, and he could
be drawn to you more.

2062
01:57:37,051 --> 01:57:40,541
And he could be curious about Gyu Ri, too.

2063
01:57:40,541 --> 01:57:44,841
But this is just the beginning,
and he's getting to know people.

2064
01:57:44,841 --> 01:57:47,581
And because your feelings grew so much...

2065
01:57:47,581 --> 01:57:50,021
You're at a different pace.

2066
01:57:50,021 --> 01:57:52,191
You're struggling with that gap.

2067
01:57:52,191 --> 01:57:54,781
Exactly. She's right on.

2068
01:57:54,781 --> 01:57:58,901
So, if you turn completely away,
I don't want your feelings to go to waste.

2069
01:57:58,901 --> 01:58:01,841
- Just...
- That's so sweet.

2070
01:58:01,841 --> 01:58:04,011
You just go at your own pace.

2071
01:58:04,011 --> 01:58:09,081
Take it slow if you think that'll make
things easier for you.

2072
01:58:09,081 --> 01:58:11,311
Min Ju is such a great friend.

2073
01:58:12,211 --> 01:58:14,051
It bothers me.

2074
01:58:14,051 --> 01:58:16,601
I'm so annoyed. He shouldn't be so pale, then.

2075
01:58:16,601 --> 01:58:18,611
So cute.

2076
01:58:18,611 --> 01:58:21,811
Or his lips shouldn't be so red.

2077
01:58:21,811 --> 01:58:25,961
- Or don't smile like that.
- Really?

2078
01:58:27,781 --> 01:58:30,021
Oh, gosh. She's so in love with him.

2079
01:58:30,021 --> 01:58:32,521
You can see if he comes back to you.

2080
01:58:32,521 --> 01:58:36,541
You can try to appease or convince yourself.

2081
01:58:37,451 --> 01:58:41,601
Let's do it. It's a month. Just hurt for a month...

2082
01:58:41,601 --> 01:58:43,991
Gosh, it hurts me so badly.

2083
01:58:43,991 --> 01:58:46,941
Just a month. Come on...

2084
01:58:48,741 --> 01:58:51,221
This is crazy.

2085
01:58:52,341 --> 01:58:55,221
Win over Wu Yeol.

2086
01:58:55,221 --> 01:58:59,221
This won't do. I'll ask him
to the movies this Sunday.

2087
01:58:59,221 --> 01:59:03,531
Yes. Be aggressive.

2088
01:59:03,531 --> 01:59:04,591
Thanks to Min Ju...

2089
01:59:04,591 --> 01:59:08,381
[What do we do...]

2090
01:59:08,381 --> 01:59:10,481
She likes him way more than we thought.

2091
01:59:10,481 --> 01:59:12,591
- I know.
- True.

2092
01:59:12,591 --> 01:59:15,111
When she said, "He shouldn't be so pale, then"...

2093
01:59:15,111 --> 01:59:17,061
It's been about a week, right?

2094
01:59:17,061 --> 01:59:20,671
A week in the house compared
to our week is so different.

2095
01:59:20,671 --> 01:59:23,251
- Probably.
- They live together.

2096
01:59:23,251 --> 01:59:25,471
And the stimulus factors can be observed

2097
01:59:25,471 --> 01:59:28,721
through the relationships
with others in the house.

2098
01:59:28,721 --> 01:59:31,441
The intensity must be out of this world.

2099
01:59:31,441 --> 01:59:36,211
I hope Min Ju's advice has
a positive impact on her.

2100
01:59:36,211 --> 01:59:38,161
From what Min Ju said...

2101
01:59:38,161 --> 01:59:41,241
So, if you turn completely away,
I don't want your feelings to go to waste.

2102
01:59:41,241 --> 01:59:44,981
Let's do it. It's a month.
Just hurt for a month...

2103
01:59:44,981 --> 01:59:46,561
You have to date in that mindset.

2104
01:59:46,561 --> 01:59:50,221
Min Ju knows how to love herself.

2105
01:59:50,221 --> 01:59:56,081
Her feelings may be overwhelming,
yet it's valuable to her how far she's come.

2106
01:59:56,081 --> 01:59:58,841
And through what Min Ju said,

2107
01:59:58,841 --> 02:00:03,621
Yu Gyeong saw Wu Yeol's
behavior more objectively

2108
02:00:03,621 --> 02:00:06,901
- and realize he's not entirely off base.
- Right, right.

2109
02:00:06,901 --> 02:00:14,101
I think she was able to realize that this is
just a part of getting to know people.

2110
02:00:14,101 --> 02:00:16,631
But I can't predict it anymore.

2111
02:00:16,631 --> 02:00:19,141
My head hurts now.

2112
02:00:19,141 --> 02:00:20,551
- Dizzy, right?
- Yes.

2113
02:00:20,551 --> 02:00:22,831
The easiest one is Seong Min.

2114
02:00:22,831 --> 02:00:24,721
Gosh, he's...

2115
02:00:24,721 --> 02:00:26,961
- Let's take the easy road.
- Go with Seong Min first.

2116
02:00:26,961 --> 02:00:29,711
Seong Min will choose Yu Gyeong.

2117
02:00:29,711 --> 02:00:32,231
I think Jun Hyeon is easy, too.

2118
02:00:32,231 --> 02:00:34,041
[Who will Jun Hyeon choose?]

2119
02:00:34,041 --> 02:00:36,571
I think So Yun.

2120
02:00:36,571 --> 02:00:39,411
He enjoyed talking to her.

2121
02:00:39,411 --> 02:00:41,551
You've become more outgoing.

2122
02:00:41,551 --> 02:00:42,991
He did become more outgoing, right?

2123
02:00:42,991 --> 02:00:44,511
He's more talkative.

2124
02:00:44,511 --> 02:00:46,221
Jun Hyeon will choose So Yun.

2125
02:00:46,221 --> 02:00:48,551
- So Yun will choose Wu Yeol.
- Totally.

2126
02:00:48,551 --> 02:00:50,591
So Yun, seriously...

2127
02:00:50,591 --> 02:00:53,871
We saw the ultimate chemistry. The best date.

2128
02:00:53,871 --> 02:00:55,741
Gosh, she has to choose him.

2129
02:00:55,741 --> 02:00:57,471
Their date was fun, too.

2130
02:00:57,471 --> 02:00:59,501
Seo Won, too. Gyu Ri.

2131
02:00:59,501 --> 02:01:01,861
They were more transparent than I thought.

2132
02:01:01,861 --> 02:01:04,581
It's getting easier now.

2133
02:01:04,581 --> 02:01:06,621
Min Ju.

2134
02:01:06,621 --> 02:01:08,701
- Min Ju...
- I don't know.

2135
02:01:08,701 --> 02:01:09,951
Isn't it Seong Min again?

2136
02:01:09,951 --> 02:01:11,811
But with Seong Min...

2137
02:01:11,811 --> 02:01:13,621
- I don't think it's Seong Min.
- No?

2138
02:01:13,621 --> 02:01:16,171
- I don't think it's Seong Min.
- I think she softened up.

2139
02:01:16,171 --> 02:01:19,191
She did soften up.

2140
02:01:19,191 --> 02:01:21,041
She did, but...

2141
02:01:21,041 --> 02:01:26,431
Min Ju will love someone
who is worthy of her feelings.

2142
02:01:26,431 --> 02:01:28,041
She said, even though it hurts.

2143
02:01:28,041 --> 02:01:32,181
As she advised Yu Gyeong,
I'm sure she thought of herself.

2144
02:01:32,181 --> 02:01:34,321
- Right. I think so.
- She must've felt that.

2145
02:01:34,321 --> 02:01:35,951
Then, it could be Seong Min.

2146
02:01:35,951 --> 02:01:39,171
I think Min Ju is honest about her feelings.

2147
02:01:39,171 --> 02:01:41,981
- Next, Gyu Ri.
- I think she'll choose Seo Won.

2148
02:01:41,981 --> 02:01:45,911
- She got a gift from him after the ride.
- He gave her vitamins.

2149
02:01:45,911 --> 02:01:47,211
Gyu Ri will choose Seo Won.

2150
02:01:47,211 --> 02:01:48,971
Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol are finished, right?

2151
02:01:48,971 --> 02:01:51,271
I don't think they're completely finished.

2152
02:01:51,271 --> 02:01:53,701
For today.

2153
02:01:53,701 --> 02:01:55,581
Why is it so easy today? It's weird.

2154
02:01:55,581 --> 02:01:58,671
Gyu Ri and Seo Won.

2155
02:01:58,671 --> 02:02:00,851
Yu Gyeong will choose Wu Yeol, right?

2156
02:02:00,851 --> 02:02:03,561
What? Wu Yeol, all of a sudden? Wait.

2157
02:02:03,561 --> 02:02:05,811
Wouldn't it be Wu Yeol?

2158
02:02:05,811 --> 02:02:08,601
She received advice from Min Ju.

2159
02:02:08,601 --> 02:02:11,851
- Wu Yeol. Definitely Wu Yeol.
- 100 percent.

2160
02:02:11,851 --> 02:02:14,401
She was wandering near his room.

2161
02:02:14,401 --> 02:02:15,871
"He shouldn't be so pale, then."

2162
02:02:15,871 --> 02:02:18,981
- "His lips shouldn't be so red."
- Wu Yeol for sure.

2163
02:02:18,981 --> 02:02:20,861
What's your concern, Eana?

2164
02:02:20,861 --> 02:02:22,791
I'm not sure. Let's go to the next one.

2165
02:02:22,791 --> 02:02:25,101
[Is that right?]

2166
02:02:25,101 --> 02:02:26,451
It's Wu Yeol.

2167
02:02:26,451 --> 02:02:28,731
But deciding this so quickly seems...

2168
02:02:28,731 --> 02:02:32,441
I don't think she can text Wu Yeol,
but I don't know who she'll text.

2169
02:02:32,441 --> 02:02:34,671
She still hasn't made up her mind, you mean?

2170
02:02:34,671 --> 02:02:37,531
After she cried at the end,
talked it out with Min Ju,

2171
02:02:37,531 --> 02:02:39,651
I think she picked Wu Yeol.

2172
02:02:39,651 --> 02:02:41,281
Yu Gyeong will choose Wu Yeol.

2173
02:02:41,281 --> 02:02:42,711
- Is it over?
- And...

2174
02:02:42,711 --> 02:02:44,671
- Wu Yeol.
- Wu Yeol remains.

2175
02:02:44,671 --> 02:02:47,541
[I don't know about this...]

2176
02:02:47,541 --> 02:02:49,441
Wu Yeol will choose So Yun.

2177
02:02:49,441 --> 02:02:51,171
I think so, too...

2178
02:02:51,171 --> 02:02:52,791
[Can't believe what he's hearing]

2179
02:02:52,791 --> 02:02:56,491
Wu Yeol was always like that.
He lives in the present.

2180
02:02:56,491 --> 02:02:58,861
If he chooses So Yun,
I'm so disappointed in Wu Yeol.

2181
02:02:58,861 --> 02:03:00,841
Based on today's events.

2182
02:03:00,841 --> 02:03:02,561
[Can't understand it]

2183
02:03:02,561 --> 02:03:06,551
He felt distant from Yu Gyeong today.

2184
02:03:06,551 --> 02:03:10,331
- Are you going to bed?
-Yeah, I'll go to bed.

2185
02:03:11,251 --> 02:03:14,131
[Did she close the door to her heart for Wu Yeol?]

2186
02:03:14,131 --> 02:03:16,151
- Want a ride to the station?
- Nope.

2187
02:03:16,151 --> 02:03:18,071
Back of Yu Gyeong that seemed so cold.

2188
02:03:18,071 --> 02:03:21,291
And Wu Yeol didn't get any texts.

2189
02:03:21,291 --> 02:03:24,101
- So, he's mad.
- He's slightly miffed at Yu Gyeong.

2190
02:03:24,101 --> 02:03:26,191
I'll trust you, Wu Yeol.

2191
02:03:26,191 --> 02:03:29,121
- Wu Yeol and So Yun.
- That's it.

2192
02:03:29,121 --> 02:03:31,111
We got it all correct.

2193
02:03:31,111 --> 02:03:33,761
This is 100 percent correct.

2194
02:03:33,761 --> 02:03:38,401
[Each has their own concern tonight]

2195
02:03:39,381 --> 02:03:40,341
[Sigh]

2196
02:03:40,341 --> 02:03:42,741
Why am I so stressed about this?

2197
02:03:42,741 --> 02:03:46,991
[The weight of the heart is
tough to put into words]

2198
02:03:47,851 --> 02:03:53,331
[Who should I convey my feelings to tonight?]

2199
02:03:54,921 --> 02:03:56,961
[Dried Sweet Potato:
It's vacation! Let's have fun!]

2200
02:03:56,961 --> 02:03:58,781
[Dried Sweet Potato]

2201
02:03:58,781 --> 02:04:00,971
- I'm so happy!
- Two days in a row.

2202
02:04:00,971 --> 02:04:02,531
That's right.

2203
02:04:02,531 --> 02:04:06,621
Seo Won pretends not to look.
He sees and puts it away.

2204
02:04:09,861 --> 02:04:10,961
[Looking]

2205
02:04:12,071 --> 02:04:14,871
[Pure Rabbit: Let's eat lots
of yummy food in Japan!]

2206
02:04:14,871 --> 02:04:19,841
[Pure Rabbit]

2207
02:04:19,841 --> 02:04:22,341
[So Yun's text went to Wu Yeol]

2208
02:04:22,341 --> 02:04:26,311
- He knows Pure Rabbit is So Yun.
- He knows.

2209
02:04:28,501 --> 02:04:30,781
[Sleepy Bear: See you tomorrow!]

2210
02:04:30,781 --> 02:04:34,751
She came back. She softened up.

2211
02:04:35,821 --> 02:04:39,411
[Seong Min's Signal Phone buzzes again]

2212
02:04:40,381 --> 02:04:43,481
[My Dog, Yellow: Good job today.
Tomorrow is going to be so fun!]

2213
02:04:44,081 --> 02:04:47,281
[My Dog, Yellow]

2214
02:04:47,281 --> 02:04:50,091
What? What happened?

2215
02:04:50,091 --> 02:04:52,571
[Shocking]

2216
02:04:52,571 --> 02:04:55,631
- Yu Gyeong is weird.
- Didn't she hear anything Min Ju said?

2217
02:04:55,631 --> 02:04:56,991
Is this wrong?

2218
02:04:56,991 --> 02:04:58,621
Wait, let's analyze Yu Gyeong.

2219
02:04:58,621 --> 02:05:02,241
How can you be so sure? All the time?

2220
02:05:02,241 --> 02:05:04,061
[We just laugh]

2221
02:05:04,061 --> 02:05:06,211
She must've decided not to text Wu Yeol.

2222
02:05:06,211 --> 02:05:09,421
- For now.
- When she sobs like that,

2223
02:05:09,421 --> 02:05:13,051
"Oh, yeah? Should I try?" She can't say that.

2224
02:05:13,051 --> 02:05:16,521
But since she talked to Min Ju...

2225
02:05:16,521 --> 02:05:17,901
[That's not enough]

2226
02:05:17,901 --> 02:05:20,401
Third-degree burn.

2227
02:05:20,401 --> 02:05:22,981
But she waited in front of his room and all.

2228
02:05:22,981 --> 02:05:25,221
I thought she was going to muster up courage.

2229
02:05:25,221 --> 02:05:28,371
She still doesn't want to text Wu Yeol...

2230
02:05:28,371 --> 02:05:31,051
What could she say? Her heavy heart...

2231
02:05:31,051 --> 02:05:33,781
But Seong Min will mistake this.

2232
02:05:33,781 --> 02:05:37,651
If she texts Wu Yeol without
any contact with him today,

2233
02:05:37,651 --> 02:05:39,811
it's like telling him, "I love you."

2234
02:05:39,811 --> 02:05:43,441
I think that's the right choice
after looking at it like this.

2235
02:05:43,441 --> 02:05:46,451
I feel bad that she can't text him.

2236
02:05:46,451 --> 02:05:48,821
[Starts writing right away]

2237
02:05:48,821 --> 02:05:51,671
[Sleepy Bear? My Dog, Yellow?]

2238
02:05:51,671 --> 02:05:55,611
Seong Min wouldn't be able to sleep over this.

2239
02:05:57,171 --> 02:05:58,501
[Getting up]

2240
02:05:58,501 --> 02:06:00,021
It's here.

2241
02:06:00,021 --> 02:06:03,271
[Salt Bread: Let's have fun in Japan]

2242
02:06:03,271 --> 02:06:07,681
[Salt Bread]

2243
02:06:08,091 --> 02:06:10,801
[Gyu Ri gets a text]

2244
02:06:10,801 --> 02:06:13,091
From Seo Won?

2245
02:06:13,091 --> 02:06:15,711
[Beluga of the Forest: I had fun]

2246
02:06:16,331 --> 02:06:20,261
[Beluga of the Forest]

2247
02:06:20,261 --> 02:06:23,391
[Failed to guess Jun Hyeon's choice]

2248
02:06:23,391 --> 02:06:25,251
- Wait.
- Who was it again?

2249
02:06:25,251 --> 02:06:27,241
Gyu Ri.

2250
02:06:27,241 --> 02:06:30,631
[Jun Hyeon texted Gyu Ri]

2251
02:06:36,261 --> 02:06:39,271
[Tired Camel: Let's have fun on our trip]

2252
02:06:39,271 --> 02:06:43,861
[Tired Camel]

2253
02:06:43,861 --> 02:06:46,881
They're becoming more fixed, right?

2254
02:06:46,881 --> 02:06:50,141
[Did they all get the texts
they were waiting for?]

2255
02:06:54,241 --> 02:06:56,661
[Busy Hamster: Take care of yourself!
Let's make great memories tomorrow!]

2256
02:06:56,661 --> 02:07:00,141
[Busy Hamster]

2257
02:07:00,141 --> 02:07:06,451
[Yu Gyeong received a text.
Who is she thinking of?]

2258
02:07:06,451 --> 02:07:08,821
[10 minutes ago]

2259
02:07:08,821 --> 02:07:11,521
[Wu Yeol sees Yu Gyeong]

2260
02:07:13,741 --> 02:07:15,901
Hi.

2261
02:07:15,901 --> 02:07:17,921
- It's been a while.
- I know.

2262
02:07:17,921 --> 02:07:19,951
After 24 hours?

2263
02:07:19,951 --> 02:07:22,911
[Gyu Ri comes upstairs]

2264
02:07:22,911 --> 02:07:26,971
I'm sure everyone took them off somewhere.

2265
02:07:26,971 --> 02:07:28,321
The timing is so...

2266
02:07:28,321 --> 02:07:31,831
- Wear these. They're small.
- Thank you.

2267
02:07:31,831 --> 02:07:33,841
She saw that.

2268
02:07:33,841 --> 02:07:38,481
- So warm. Just kidding.
- I warmed them up for you.

2269
02:07:38,481 --> 02:07:43,981
[Distance felt in the same space]

2270
02:07:43,981 --> 02:07:45,931
She's going back into her room.

2271
02:07:45,931 --> 02:07:48,661
What a twist of fate.

2272
02:07:48,661 --> 02:07:54,801
[She feels smaller as her feelings
become more transparent]

2273
02:07:54,801 --> 02:07:58,051
- Oh, no.
- Crazy.

2274
02:07:58,051 --> 02:08:00,981
Did you see how she couldn't even say one thing?

2275
02:08:00,981 --> 02:08:05,631
[Deeper and more complicated feelings]

2276
02:08:05,631 --> 02:08:08,201
Gosh, so crazy.

2277
02:08:09,751 --> 02:08:12,201
And they have to go on a trip. My gosh...

2278
02:08:12,201 --> 02:08:15,871
I'm dying to know what will
happen in the next episode.

2279
02:08:15,871 --> 02:08:17,541
I know. How can we wait?

2280
02:08:17,541 --> 02:08:20,171
This is trouble. Oh, no.

2281
02:08:21,451 --> 02:08:23,691
- It's going to be a mess.
- It's big trouble.

2282
02:08:23,691 --> 02:08:26,431
I'm dying to know.

2283
02:08:26,431 --> 02:08:28,781
Wow, daebak!

2284
02:08:28,781 --> 02:08:32,321
- What lovely weather!
- It's Japan.

2285
02:08:32,321 --> 02:08:35,121
After we come back from Japan...

2286
02:08:36,161 --> 02:08:38,961
- I think...
- Something will happen?

2287
02:08:39,871 --> 02:08:41,791
Can I call you "noona'?

2288
02:08:41,791 --> 02:08:43,561
How? Just smile?

2289
02:08:43,561 --> 02:08:45,631
I'll smile a lot from now on.

2290
02:08:47,511 --> 02:08:52,451
The person I'm interested in likes someone else.

2291
02:08:52,451 --> 02:08:54,611
I felt a little jealous.

2292
02:08:54,611 --> 02:08:57,811
I want to spend this evening with you.

2293
02:08:57,811 --> 02:08:59,611
Me, too.

2294
02:08:59,611 --> 02:09:01,531
I never got to talk to Yu Gyeong.

2295
02:09:01,531 --> 02:09:03,011
Me, too. Yu Gyeong.

2296
02:09:03,011 --> 02:09:06,161
[Will they get hurt from their
expectations that differ from reality?]

2297
02:09:06,691 --> 02:09:09,431
Do you like familiarity or something new?

2298
02:09:09,431 --> 02:09:11,151
I don't know.

2299
02:09:11,151 --> 02:09:12,451
I'm scared.

2300
02:09:12,451 --> 02:09:15,641
I can't read him.

2301
02:09:15,641 --> 02:09:20,221
If I really like her,
even if she doesn't accept me,

2302
02:09:21,221 --> 02:09:23,331
I think I'll still love her.

2303
02:09:23,331 --> 02:09:25,221
I don't believe in fate.

2304
02:09:25,221 --> 02:09:27,401
You can change fate.

2305
02:09:27,401 --> 02:09:31,131
Should we try speaking casually?

2306
02:09:31,131 --> 02:09:32,781
I'd like that.

2307
02:09:32,781 --> 02:09:35,381
I can't help it if things don't work out.

2308
02:09:35,381 --> 02:09:37,771
I'll try my best to the end.

2309
02:09:39,531 --> 02:09:43,011
Let's walk through the thorny field.

2310
02:09:43,941 --> 02:09:47,161
When we return on Saturday...

2311
02:09:47,161 --> 02:09:49,531
I want to see a movie with you.
